column791: Palabora Mining Company Limited, through its subsidiary, Palabora Copper Proprietary Limited, engages in the mining, extraction, and sale of copper, magnetite, and associated by-products. The company operates a copper mine, smelter, and refinery complex in the Limpopo Province, South Africa.

Nedbank Group Limited, through its subsidiary, Nedbank Limited, provides various banking products and services in South Africa. It offers personal banking solutions, including savings deposits and investment accounts; home and personal loans, student loans, vehicle finance, private wealth finance solutions, overdrafts, and credit cards; and investment plans and services, financial and estate planning services, and wills and trust services, as well as professional banking, wealth advisory and investment management, non-resident and embassy banking, unit trust, offshore portfolio, investment banking, and foreign exchange services. The company also provides business banking services, such as business and tender accounts; call, fixed, and flexi deposits; loans and structured solutions; value added services; payments and receipts, documentary credits and collections, guarantees, and trade finance; card and cash solutions; treasury solutions; cash management, electronic banking, and merchant payment and support services; life, asset, income and credit protection, funeral, business cover, liability cover, revenue cover, and owners' insurance products; and commodities, equities, fixed income, and structured credit products. In addition, the company offers corporate banking services comprising aircraft, asset based, carbon, export credit, global commodity, infrastructure, energy, telecoms, leveraged, mining, oil and gas, private equity, and public sector finance; corporate lending and advances, and specialized distribution products; custodial services; corporate finance and debt advisory services; and beta solutions, as well as corporate and institutional investments. The company was formerly known as Nedcor Limited and changed its name to Nedbank Group Limited in 2005. The company was founded in 1973 and is headquartered in Sandown, South Africa. Nedbank Group Limited is a subsidiary of Old Mutual Life Assurance Company (SA) Limited.

Sycom Property Fund operates as a closed-end property unit trust in South Africa. As of September 30, 2005, its portfolio consisted of 17 properties in retail and commercial office sectors. The fund's retail portfolio, which comprised investment in four regional shopping centers, contributed 44% of gross property income and office portfolio comprised the remaining 56%. Geographically, 68% of the properties were located in Greater Johannesburg with the balance of 32% located in the Western Cape. The fund is managed by Sycom Property Fund Managers Limited. Sycom Property Fund was founded in 1986 and is based in Pretoria, South Africa.

Fountainhead Property Trust operates as a closed-end investment trust in South Africa. The trust primarily invests in retail properties comprising shopping centres; office properties consisting of office parks and office buildings; industrial properties that includes industrial buildings, such as warehouses and factories; and hospital and hotel properties. Allan Gray Property Trust Management Limited serves as the manager of the trust. Fountainhead Property Trust was founded in 1983 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

MMI Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an insurance-based financial services company in South Africa and internationally. The company operates through Momentum Retail, Metropolitan Retail, Corporate and Public Sector, International, and Shareholder Capital segments. It provides wealth creation, risk, and savings solutions, as well as short-term insurance and open medical scheme solutions to customers in the upper retail and the small business segments; and savings, income generation, risk, and funeral products and solutions to entry-level markets. The company also offers solutions to enhance profitability and sustainability, as well as to protect asset base to medium and large corporates, affinity groups, labor unions, and public sector institutions. In addition, it provides Hello Doctor, a mobile health service that provides preventative care and gives people the ability to connect with a doctor to make informed decisions about their health and wellness; managed care and administration services under the CareCross brand; wellness and rewards programs under the Multiply brand; and structured insurance products, traditional cell captive facilities, reinsurance, and related services under the Guardrisk brand. Further, the company operates as a property development and property services company under the Eris brand. The company is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa.

ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd manufactures and sells long and flat steel products. The company operates through Flat Steel Products, Long Steel Products, and Coke and Chemicals segments. It offers flat steel products, including hot rolled plates, hot and cold rolled coils, galvanized coils, color coils, electrogalvanized coils, and tinplate coils. The company also provides foundry products that include castings, such as air injection tubes, door bodies, fire bars, pallet cars, pallet frames, goose necks, etc. for coke ovens, direct reduction, sinter plant, and blast furnaces, as well as the hot and cold mills. In addition, it offers long steel products comprising fencing profiles, forgings, hexagon bars, hollow bars, mining bars, rails, reinforcing bars/Y bars, rounds and squares, special profiles, structural and heavy structural sections, window sections, wire rods, billets and blooms, hot-finished and cold-drawn seamless tubes, and forged products; and tubular products, which comprise hot rolled seamless line pipes and OCTG, hot rolled boiler tubes, and cold drawn precision products. Further, the company provides commercial coke for the ferro-alloy industry; processes and beneficiates metallurgical and steel by-products, including coal tar; and provides commercial-grade coking coal. It serves clients in agricultural, armament, automotive, bolt and nut, chains, construction, engineering, furniture and appliance, mining, packaging, piping, renewable energy, roofing and cladding, tubing, food and beverages, infrastructure, defense, and oil and gas industries primarily in the Republic of South Africa and sub-Saharan Africa. The company was formerly known as Mittal Steel South Africa Limited and changed its name to ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd in October 2006. The company was founded in 1928 and is headquartered in Vanderbijlpark, the Republic of South Africa. ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd is a subsidiary of ArcelorMittal Holdings AG.

AVI Limited, together with its subsidiaries, primarily manufactures, markets, and distributes food and FMCG products in South Africa. It operates through Entyce Beverages, Snackworks, I&J, Personal Care, and Footwear & Apparel segments. The company provides hot beverages, sweet and savoury biscuits and snacks, frozen convenience foods, out-of-home ranges, personal care products, cosmetics, shoes, accessories, and fashion apparel. It offers beverages under the Five Roses, Freshpak, House of Coffees, Frisco, Koffiehuis, Ellis Brown, Trinco, Ciro, Lavazza, and Douwe Egberts brands; biscuits and snacks under the Bakers, Provita, Willards, and Jumping Jack brands; frozen food under the I&J brand; and personal care products under the Yardley and Lentheric brands. The company also provides footwear and apparel under the Spitz, Carvela, Green Cross, Kurt Geiger, Lacoste, Tosoni, Nina Roche, Saffron Browne, and Gant brands. AVI Limited is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

AECI Ltd operates as an explosives and specialty chemicals company in Africa, South East Asia, the United States, and Australia. It operates through Explosives, Specialty Chemicals, and Property segments. The Explosives segment develops, produces, and supplies commercial explosives, initiating systems, and blasting services for the mining, quarrying, and construction markets. The Specialty Chemicals segment supplies specialty chemical raw materials and related services for use across a range of customers in the manufacturing, mining, water treatment, agricultural, and general industrial sectors. The Property segment provides leasing services; and utilities and other services, such as centralized generation and distribution of steam, security services, potable water, electricity, effluent handling, and a rail network, as well as manages properties. The company also offers water treatment solutions, agrochemicals, and juice-based products and ingredients. AECI Ltd was founded in 1924 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Tongaat Hulett Limited, an agriculture and agri-processing company, engages in land management, property development, and agriculture activities primarily in Zimbabwe, Swaziland, Mozambique, South Africa, and internationally. It produces and sells various refined carbohydrate products from sugarcane and maize; sweeteners; energy and supplementary feeds to the livestock farming community under the Voermol brand, using bagasse and molasses; and corn starch, glucose, and other related products under the Amryal, Hydex, Vaalgold, and Gluten 60 brands. The company offers white and brown sugar products under the Huletts, SunSweet, Blue Crystal, and Marathon brands. It also engages in the production of ethanol; and generation of electricity from bagasse. Tongaat Hulett Limited was founded in 1875 and is based in Tongaat, South Africa.

Adcock Ingram Holdings Limited manufactures, markets, and distributes healthcare products primarily in Sub-Saharan Africa and India. It offers a portfolio of prescription medicines, generic products, critical care, over-the-counter and consumer products, intravenous solutions, blood collection products, and renal dialysis systems. The company provides pharmaceutical products in a range of therapeutic classes, such as women's health, antiretroviral, allergies, dermatology, cardiovascular, central nervous system, respiratory, ophthalmic, urology, pain, mental health, gastrointestinal, infections, pain and inflammation, colds and flu, personal care, supplements and energy, feminine hygiene, and digestive well-being. It also manufactures and supplies hospital and critical care products, including intravenous fluids, renal dialysis systems, products for the storage of blood and blood components, infusion systems, and accessories. Adcock Ingram Holdings Limited was founded in 1890 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Edcon Acquisition Proprietary Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a non-food retailer in South Africa. Its Edgars division operates stores that primarily sell clothing, footwear, cosmetics, mobile phones, homewares, and accessories to middle to upper income consumers. The company's Jet division sells value merchandise, including clothing, footwear, mobile phones, cosmetics, homewares, and accessories targeted at lower to middle income consumers under the names of Jet and Jet Mart stores. The Specialty division offers stationery, books, magazines, greeting cards, music, toys, photographic, digital equipment, cosmetics, mobile phones, homewares clothing, footwear, and accessories to middle to upper income consumers. This division operates CNA, Red Square, Boardmans, Edgars Active, Edgars Shoe Gallery, Legit, and the mono-branded stores. Its Edgars Zimbabwe division manufactures and retails clothing, footwear, cosmetics, mobile phones, and accessories to lower to middle income consumers and middle to upper consumers. The company's manufacturing division manufactures apparel and footwear focusing on mid to high-end garments of woven construction and footwear. This division offers ladies and men's outerwear and footwear. Its Credit and Financial Services division offers consumer credit and insurance products to trade debtors. As of March 25, 2017, the company had 1,343 stores, including 187 stores in Namibia, Botswana, Lesotho, Swaziland, Mozambique, Ghana, Zimbabwe, and Zambia. Edcon Acquisition Proprietary Limited was founded in 1929 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. Edcon Acquisition Proprietary Limited operates as a subsidiary of K2016470295 (South Africa) Limited.

PPC Ltd, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells cementitious, aggregate, lime and limestone, and fly ash products in South Africa, Botswana, Mozambique, Zimbabwe, Rwanda, and the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Oceana Group Limited operates as a fishing company. It operates through Canned Fish and Fishmeal; Fishmeal and Fish Oil; Horse Mackerel and Hake; Lobster, Squid and French Fries; and Commercial Cold Storage and Logistics segments. The company engages in fishing for inshore pelagic species, such as anchovy, the gulf menhaden species, redeye herring, and pilchard; the production, marketing, and distribution of fishmeal and canned fish products under the Lucky Star label, as well as pet foods under the Lucky Pet brand; and provision of fishmeal and fish oil for use in animal and aquaculture feed, fertilizers, pharmaceutical, and chemical industries. It is also involved in the fishing, processing, procurement, distribution, and trading of caught demersal species, such as horse mackerel, hake, monk, kingklip, and other by-catch products. In addition, the company produces and exports live and frozen South African rock lobster, and frozen squid products; and produces and markets nitrogen frozen lobsters and lobster tails, and French fries. Further, it owns and operates 12 public refrigerated warehouse facilities, as well as engages in fruit handling, blast freezing, and transportation activities; and offers logistic services. The company provides cold storage for products, such as poultry, fish, meat, vegetables, dairy, margarine, and fruit. It offers its products to individuals, retailers, wholesalers, importers, exporters, restaurants, food producers, feed manufacturers, and pet owners in Africa, the United States, Asia, the European Union, and Australia. Oceana Group Limited was incorporated in 1918 and is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Reunert Limited operates in the fields of electrical engineering, information communication technologies (ICT), and applied electronics in South Africa, Australia, Lesotho, Sweden, the United States, Zambia, and Zimbabwe. Its Electrical Engineering segment designs, manufactures, installs, and maintains power cables; manufactures and supplies copper and optical fiber telecommunications cables and cable ducts, as well as low-voltage distribution, protection, and control equipment; and supplies high and medium-voltage switchgears and transformers. This segment also provides power installations services; designs and manufactures overhead aluminum conductors; and manufactures copper casted rods. It serves mining, utilities, commercial, industrial, residential, retail, petrochemical, transport, power, and building sectors, as well as electrical contractors, equipment manufacturers, fixed and mobile network operators, municipalities, and parastatals. The company's ICT segment provides data and voice communication and network services and solutions, as well as asset-based rental solutions; and distributes office automation and telecommunication systems. This segment comprises corporate and retail customers, small and medium enterprises, government, and state-owned entities, non-profit organizations. Its Applied Electronics segment specializes in tactical VHF/UHF/HF communication systems; designs and manufactures fuses and related defense products for artillery, mortar, naval, and aircraft weapon systems; develops and manufactures ground and naval search and tracking radar systems; and designs and manufactures mining radar sensor systems used in open-cast mining. This segment manufactures and supplies remote-controlled weapon platforms; and supplies system engineering and logistic support services in telecommunications, radar, satellite, mining, fare management, and transportation fields. Reunert Limited was founded in 1888 and is headquartered in Woodmead, South Africa.

Hudaco Industries Limited, together with its subsidiaries, imports and distributes branded automotive, industrial, and electrical consumable products in the southern African region. It operates through two segments, Consumer-Related Products and Engineering Consumables. The Consumer-Related Products segment distributes clutch kits, automotive ignition leads, oil and hydraulic seals, wheels, brake and clutch hydraulics, mountings, bushes, hydraulic repair kits, cylinders, hoses, CV joints, wheel hubs, suspension components, and vehicle components to the automotive and industrial after-market; maintenance free lead acid, stand-by and solar batteries; power tools, marine engines, survey equipment, rivets, and fasteners; and intruder detection, access control, and related CCTV equipment, including design and integration of systems, fiber-optics, fire detection, and video over IP installations. This segment also distributes professional mobile radio equipment and radio systems integrators; wireless networking, VoIP, and video products; and communication management software, solutions, and equipment. The Engineering Consumables segment distributes diesel engines and spares, as well as support services; and geared motors, beltings, hydraulics, drivetrains, filtration solutions, kits and accessories, pneumatics, industrial hoses, conveyor drive pulleys, variable speed drives, special engineering steels, specialized thermoplastic pipes and fittings, gear pumps, ferrous and non-ferrous castings, electrical cablings, plugs, and related products to the manufacturing, mining, and agricultural aftermarkets. This segment also distributes bearings, chains, seals, geared motors, electric motors, and transmission products. The company primarily serves wholesale and retail, automotive, manufacturing, mining, security, alternative energy, construction, public, agricultural, and other sectors. Hudaco Industries Limited was founded in 1891 and is headquartered in Edenvale, South Africa.

The Foschini Group Limited, an investment holding company, operates independent chain-stores in South Africa and internationally. Metair Investments Limited manufactures, assembles, distributes, and retails energy storage products and automotive components in Africa, Europe, Turkey, the Middle East, and Russia. It offers energy storage products, including automotive and industrial batteries, solar systems, back-up systems, standby systems, charging systems, battery distribution networks, and lithium-ion starter batteries and mining cap lamps for automotive, telecom, utility, mining, retail, and materials/products handling sectors, as well as original equipment manufacturers. The company also provides automotive components, such as air-conditioning and climate control systems, cooling modules, washer systems, charge air coolers, and reserve tanks; radiators; air cleaners; wiper systems; electronic control units; starter motors; hydraulics, brake pads, brake discs, and brake shoes; coil springs, leaf springs, stabilizers, and torsion bars; and headlights, tail lights, reflectors, commercial lighting products, streetlights, and warehouse lights. Its automotive components also comprise plastic injection moldings, plastic bins/storage, and chrome plating on plastics; automotive cable, automotive wire, and wiring harnesses; combination meter/instrument clusters; and front-end modules, shock absorbers, struts, and track control arms. The company provides automotive components for use in the assembly of new vehicles; and industrial and utility sectors. Metair Investments Limited was founded in 1948 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Pick n Pay Stores Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the retail of food, clothes, general merchandise, pharmaceuticals, and liquor. The company operates in two segments, South Africa and Rest of Africa. It owns, franchises, and invests in supermarkets, hypermarkets, local stores, clothing stores, liquor stores, pharmacy stores, spaza stores, express convenience stores, superstores, build stores, and punch stores under the Pick n Pay and Boxer brands, which offer groceries, clothing, food products, liquor, health and beauty products, pharmaceuticals, building and hardware, and general merchandise. The company also offers its products through online. In addition, it acquires and develops retail and distribution sites; and provides value-added services comprising third-party bill payments, financial transactions at till point, electricity, ATM, lottery, and ticketing services, as well as sells air time and gift cards. Pick n Pay Stores Limited operates a network of 1,560 owned and franchised stores in South Africa, Botswana, Lesotho, Namibia, Swaziland, Zambia, and Zimbabwe. The company was founded in 1967 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Pick n Pay Stores Limited is a subsidiary of Pick n Pay Holdings Limited RF.

RCL Foods Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in the food business in South Africa. It processes and markets chicken under the Rainbow, Farmer Brown, Rainbow FoodSolutions, Epol, and Cobb brand names. The company also manufactures, markets, and distributes a range of food products comprising grain and edible oil-based products, sorghum, peanut butter, rusks, and pet foods, as well as salad dressings, dips, and spreads; meat pies under the Pieman's brand; and specialty products, such as sandwiches, muffins, desserts, snack foods, scones, rye breads, cake products, pastries, and croissants. In addition, it produces maize based health drink under the Mageu No 1, Smooth, Phuzimpilo, and Mnandi brands; and operates seven bakeries, one flour mill, and one maize mill. JD Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, primarily engages in the retail sale of furniture, household appliances, consumer electronic and technology goods, and building materials and do-it-yourself products primarily in South Africa. The company is also involved in the provision of insurance services and contact centre solutions; and retail of new and pre-owned motor vehicles, parts, insurance, and accessories, as well as offers servicing and short term car rental services. ELB Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides engineering solutions to the mining, minerals, power, port, construction, and industrial sectors in the fields of materials handling, mineral separation, industrial projects, and power solutions in Africa and internationally. It operates in three segments: Equipment, Engineering Services, and Australasia. The company supplies construction equipment, such as trenching and horizontal directional drilling equipment, pneumatic piercing tools, backhoe loaders, compact wheel loaders, skid-steer loaders, motor graders, compact excavators, telescopic handlers, and compaction equipment. It also offers earthmoving equipment consisting of bulldozers, wheel loaders, and open cast mining trucks; and mining/recycling equipment, including mobile and static screening plants, mobile and static crushing plants, hydraulic drill rigs, hydraulic breakers, excavator attachments, recycling systems, block makers, heavy-duty rotary barrel screens, telescopic conveyor belts, vertical shaft impact crushers, screener-crusher buckets, modular plants, and washing systems. In addition, the company provides engineering services in the areas of bulk material handling, industrial projects, engineered technologies, mechanical/structural erection, conveyer maintenance, and logistics, as well as electrical, control, and instrumentation. Further, it imports, distributes, and maintains underground and utility construction equipment, and green waste processing equipment. The company was formerly known as Edward L Bateman Ltd. ELB Group Limited was founded in 1903 and is based in Boksburg, South Africa.

Petmin Limited, a multi-commodity mining company, produces and sells metallurgical anthracite in South Africa and internationally. It operates through two segments, Anthracite and Expansion Projects. The company holds interests in the Somkhele anthracite mine located to the northwest of Richards Bay in KwaZulu-Natal; the North Atlantic Iron Corporation project, an iron sands deposit that produces and supplies merchant pig iron in Labrador, Canada; and the Veremo pig iron project located near Stofberg in Mpumalanga Province, South Africa. It also exports its products. Petmin Limited was incorporated in 1972 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. As of May 31, 2017, Petmin Limited was taken private.

Sasfin Holdings Limited provides banking and financial services to entrepreneurs, corporates, and high net-worth individuals primarily in South Africa. The company operates through Business Banking, Transactional Banking and Treasury, Wealth, Capital, and Commercial Solutions divisions. The Business Banking division offers equipment, taxi, and trade and debtor finance services. The Transactional Banking and Treasury division provides transactional banking products, such as deposits, transactional accounts, and debit cards; and treasury products and services. The Wealth division provides portfolio management and stockbroking, financial planning, asset management, asset consulting, healthcare, and fixed income products and services, as well as money market services. The Capital division offers private and property equity, and corporate finance services. The Commercial Solutions division offers foreign exchange, incentives, short-term insurance, and logistics services. Sasfin Holdings Limited was founded in 1951 and is headquartered in Waverley, South Africa.

Famous Brands Limited, through its subsidiaries, operates as a quick service and casual dining restaurant franchisor. The company operates through Franchising and Development, and Supply Chain divisions. Its casual dining brand portfolio comprises Wimpy, Mugg & Bean, Europa, Fego Caffe, Pubs, Tashas, Vovo Telo, House of Coffees, NetCafe, Keg, Turn 'n Tender, Coffee Couture, The Bread Basket, Mythos, PAUL, Lupa, Salsa Mexican Grill, Gourmet Burger Kitchen, 14 on Chartwell, and Catch; and quick service brand portfolio include Steers, Debonairs Pizza, Fishaways, Milky Lane, Giramundo, Mr Biggs, and Wakaberry. The company operates 2,782 franchised restaurants in South Africa, Rest of Africa, the United Kingdom, and the Middle East. It also manufactures and supplies meat and chicken products, bread and bakery items, coffee, cheese, sauces and spices, ice creams, and fruit juices to its franchisees, as well as to food service and retail customers. The company was formerly known as Steers Holdings Limited and changed its name to Famous Brands Limited in 2004. Famous Brands Limited is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

It also manufactures and supplies meat and chicken products, bread and bakery items, coffee, cheese, sauces and spices, ice creams, and fruit juices to its franchisees, as well as to food service and retail customers. The company was formerly known as Steers Holdings Limited and changed its name to Famous Brands Limited in 2004. Famous Brands Limited is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Alviva Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures, distributes, and supports information and communication technology (ICT) hardware, software, and infrastructure products. The company operates through ICT Distribution, Services and Solutions, Financial Services, and Group Central Services segments. It offers servers, personal computers, notebooks, tablets, and mobile phones; copiers and printers; security, CCTV, fire detection and prevention, and access control systems; and office automation products, hardware and software products, and implementation and structured finance solutions. The company also provides managed services, technology solution integration, and business applications; and connectivity, communication, cloud, and software development services. In addition, it offers a range of financial products, including operating rentals for technology based equipment, hire and service agreements of equipment and ancillary services, insurance of technology based goods, and short term project finance of equipment. Further, the company distributes server racking, copper, fiber, wireless, and related network hardware; and structured cabling solutions and purpose-built electronic enclosures, as well as complementary infrastructure products, such as media converters, optical fiber CCTV, and co-axial for telecommunications, data, and telephony applications. Additionally, it offers rooftop and ground solar installation services for corporate customers. Alviva Holdings Limited operates in South Africa, Botswana, Namibia, Zambia, and Mozambique. The company was formerly known as Pinnacle Holdings Limited and changed its name to Alviva Holdings Limited in March 2017. Alviva Holdings Limited was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Netcare Limited operates private hospitals in South Africa and the United Kingdom. It provides hospital, healthcare, and renal care networks, as well as emergency medical services. The company also offers occupational health and employee wellness services; and medical management services at commercial, industrial, construction, and mining sites. In addition, it operates primary care facilities for group medical practices, which provides access to general practitioners and dentists, radiology, pathology, pharmacy, physiotherapy, and day clinics. Further, the company provides dialysis services to patients with compromised kidney function; and operates retail pharmacies. As of December 6, 2016, the company operated 114 hospitals in South Africa, the United Kingdom, Lesotho, and Mozambique. Netcare Limited was incorporated in 1996 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

AFGRI Limited offers a range of products and services to farmers, producers, and users of agricultural products in South Africa. It operates through three segments: AFGRI Agri Services, AFGRI Financial Services, and AFGRI Foods. It supplies a range of mechanized equipment tailored to the needs of commercial farmers; and provides a range of farming inputs, agricultural, home and garden, outdoor, and DIY products, including selected building materials and services to farmers, week-end farmers, small-holding owners, and the general public through retail outlets. It is also involved in handling and storage of grain in South Africa and Zambia; procurement and sale of agricultural commodities; and the provision of collateral management, stock monitoring, storage, and inspections services to financial institutions, insurers, commodity traders, and farmers. It offers various financial solutions, such as foreign exchange, trade finance, currency and interest rate hedging, price risk management, specialized/corporate finance, and debt origination and restructuring services; provides broking services; and supplies thermal coal. It also provides farmer lending products and insurance brokerage services. Additionally, it manufactures and sells animal feeds primarily for the poultry, dairy, beef, sheep, and pet food markets; produces grits for the snack industry; and supplies poultry meat products. It also crushes, extracts, refines, and processes soya beans, cotton seeds, and sunflower seeds into various edible oils and fats; soya, sunflower, cotton oil cakes for animal feed; high protein defatted soya flour; and texturised soya protein for human consumption. It operates approximately 65 retail stores. It was formerly known as Oos-Transvaalse Landboukooperasie and changed its name to AFGRI Limited in 2003. It was founded in 1923 and is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa. As of March 31, 2014, AFGRI Limited operates as a subsidiary of AgriGroupe Holdings Proprietary Limited.

Andulela Investment Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the processing and distribution of steel products in Southern Africa. The company offers steel products, including welded universal columns or beams and T-beams; a range of roofing solutions; fencing and wire products; tubing and cold formed flat and long products; and value added services. The company is based in Sandton, South Africa. Andulela Investment Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Newshelf 1005 Proprietary Limited.

Illovo Sugar Limited produces and sells sugar and downstream products. The company offers industrial sugar, including refined bulk sugar primarily to soft drink, confectionery, canning, and re-packing customers; refined and brown pre-pack sugar under the Illovo, Whitespoon, and Bwana Sukari names for retail and wholesale customers; bulk raw sugar for refining; specialty sugars; and syrup products. Its downstream products include ethanol, furfural and furfuryl alcohol, diacetyl, 2.3-pentanedione, agricultural nematicides, natural methanol, ethanol potable extra neutral alcohol, anhydrous alcohol, rectified extra neutral alcohol, industrial alcohol, and lactulose. The company's downstream products also comprise Crop Guard that is used as an agricultural contact nematicide at planting; MultiGuard Protect, which is developed and marketed as an agricultural contact-nematicide; Protect that is used as a nematicide and fungicide prior to planting; and BioMass Sugar, which is used as phytofortifiers/soil improvers or as liquid organic fertilizers. It is also involved in cane growing and electricity exports activities. The company markets its products in Malawi, Mozambique, South Africa, Swaziland, Tanzania, and Zambia. Illovo Sugar Limited also exports its products primarily to the European Union and the United States. The company is headquartered in Durban, South Africa. Illovo Sugar Limited is a subsidiary of ABF Overseas Limited.

Assore Limited, a mining holding company, engages in base minerals and metals ventures business. The Bidvest Group Limited operates as a services, trading, and distribution company. It operates through seven divisions: Automotive, Commercial Products, Electrical, Financial Services, Freight, Office & Print, and Services. It retails motor vehicles, including passenger cars, SUVs, and trucks, as well as provides parts and tires support services; and distributes electrical, cable and allied products, and solutions and services for corporate, commercial, industrial, and mining customers, as well as for residential and large-scale infrastructural projects. The company also offers various banking and financial products and services to corporate and individual customers; air freight and ocean freight services; logistics and supply chain solutions; and transport, warehousing, stevedoring, container and bulk handling, customs clearing and forwarding, and ship agency services. In addition, it manufactures packaging products, fasteners and closures, self-adhesive tapes, and catering equipment; manufactures and distributes brushware and consumables, as well as distributes machinery and accessories to the clothing industry; distributes office products and furniture, office automation, and software solutions, as well as print, packaging, labelling, and communication products; and distributes food products. Further, the company offers facility management, security, industrial, and allied services; horse-mackerel, canned pilchards, oysters, and other fish products; new and pre-owned vehicles, financing and insurance products, parts and accessories, and after-sales services; foreign exchange services, prepaid world currency cards, and money transfer services; and IT services, including data management, networking, servers, software, hardware, and IT related services. Additionally, it provides property management and development, and assistance services. The Bidvest Group Limited was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

African Media Entertainment Limited operates as a radio broadcasting company in South Africa. The company's Algoa FM broadcasts music, news and gossip, sports information, and local traffic and weather information in the Eastern Cape; and OFM offers adult contemporary and golden oldie sounds to deliver an upscale audience between the ages of 25 and 49 in Free State, North West Province, Northern Cape, northern KZN, and southern Gauteng. It also operates United Stations, a specialist radio sales house; and RadioHeads, a radio station that provides radio solutions, including media planning and buying, creative strategy, and copywriting, as well as an editing suite to create final product. The company is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Mine Restoration Investments Limited, an environmental services company, focuses on the abatement of environmental impacts of the mining industry in South Africa. It is involved in coal fines screening, agglomerating, and processing and briquetting, as well as acid mine drainage activities. The company was formerly known as Capricorn Investment Holdings Limited and changed its name to Mine Restoration Investments Limited in April 2012. Mine Restoration Investments Limited was founded in 2006 and is based in Rosebank, South Africa.

column786: Cnr Barlow Road and Caveleros Drive
column791: Distribution and Warehousing Network Limited operates in the building materials and fixtures sector primarily in the Republic of South Africa. It operates through Trading and Manufacturing segments. The company engages in the manufacture and wholesale trade of hardware, sanitaryware, bathroomware, plumbing, kitchen, and other building materials. It is also involved in the manufacture and wholesale trade of engineering, civil products, piping systems, valves, and related accessories. In addition, the company offers warehousing, distribution, marketing, IT support, pre-packaging and packaging, merchandising, logistical, and HR services. In addition, the company exports its products to approximately 50 countries in sub-Saharan Africa, Asia, Australia, Europe, the Middle East, New Zealand, and South America. Distribution and Warehousing Network Limited is headquartered in Germiston, the Republic of South Africa.

Cullinan Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a tourism and leisure company in South Africa. The company operates through three segments: Travel and Tourism, Marine and Boating, and Financial Services. It offers wholesale, retail, and coaching and touring travel services. The company also provides marine and boating equipment to boat builders and wholesalers, as well as operates two retail shops in Cape Town. In addition, it offers credit, bridging, and marine finance. The company was founded in 1901 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. Cullinan Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Alpine Asset Management Limited.

Grindrod Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in freight services, shipping, trading, and financial services businesses worldwide. The company's Freight Services division offers freight logistics services, such as road transportation, rail, intermodal solutions, warehousing, storage, stevedoring, seafreight, ships agency, travel agency, and traditional logistics services; and operates terminals and ports. This division provides its services for the movement of dry-bulk, bulk liquid, containerized cargo, and vehicles along import/export corridors. Its Shipping division operates a fleet of owned, long-term chartered, and joint-venture dry-bulk, liquid-bulk, container, and bunker vessels. This division focuses on moving dry bulk cargo, such as minerals, coal, ores, and agricultural products, as well as clean petroleum products. The company's Financial Services division offers commercial lending solutions, including term loans, mezzanine finance, and equity funding; invoice discounting and trade finance products; cash deposits, investment products, and exchange traded funds; and commercial and industrial property finance, property private equity, and property investment options. This division also provides card solutions; preference-share investments and treasury deposits; corporate finance products; and asset management services, including wealth management services for private clients and institutional fund management services. Grindrod Limited is based in Durban, South Africa.

Investec Limited, a specialist bank and asset manager, provides a range of financial products and services to South Africa, the United Kingdom, Europe, Asia/Australia, and internationally. It operates through three divisions: Asset Management, Wealth & Investment, and Specialist Bank. The Asset Management division manages investments of private and public sector pension funds, insurers and corporates, and foundations and central banks, as well as intermediaries serving individual investors through equity, fixed income, multi-asset, and alternative investments. The Wealth & Investment division provides wealth management, portfolio management, private office, and stockbroking services to individuals, families, trusts, and charities, as well as alternative investment, investment advisory, electronic trading, and retirement and succession planning services. The Specialist Banking division offers private banking products and services, such as deposits, lending and investment products, transactional banking and foreign exchange services; corporate and institutional banking services, including treasury and trading, specialized lending, funds, debt capital markets, institutional research sales and trading, and advisory services; and property investment, and property investment fund management services. The company was founded in 1974 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. Investec Limited is a subsidiary of Investec Group Limited.

The Asset Management division manages investments of private and public sector pension funds, insurers and corporates, and foundations and central banks, as well as intermediaries serving individual investors through equity, fixed income, multi-asset, and alternative investments. The Wealth & Investment division provides wealth management, portfolio management, private office, and stockbroking services to individuals, families, trusts, and charities, as well as alternative investment, investment advisory, electronic trading, and retirement and succession planning services. The Specialist Banking division offers private banking products and services, such as deposits, lending and investment products, transactional banking and foreign exchange services; corporate and institutional banking services, including treasury and trading, specialized lending, funds, debt capital markets, institutional research sales and trading, and advisory services; and property investment, and property investment fund management services. The company was founded in 1974 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. Investec Limited is a subsidiary of Investec Group Limited.

Invicta Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, distributes engineering consumables, and provides technical services and solutions in Southern Africa and Singapore. It operates through Capital Equipment and Engineering Solutions segments. It distributes engineering consumables, including bearings, seals and gaskets, power transmissions, fasteners, geared and electric drives, and tools; fluid technology products and solutions, such as hydraulic, pneumatic, filtration, and lubrication; and technical design, on-site installation, maintenance, breakdown, and condition monitoring, as well as design engineering and failure analysis services. The company also distributes industrial gearbox units; tools and equipment, including personal protective equipment, lifting, and welding products; vibrator motors, and tensioning and suspension systems; vibrating equipment; automotive components; and electrical and alternative power solutions. In addition, it engages in the wholesale and retail distribution of agricultural machinery, implements and related spares, heavy earthmoving machinery for construction and mining applications, and material handling equipment and related spares, as well as turf-grooming machinery, utility vehicles, and related spares; and the distribution of after-market replacement parts, ground engaging tools, undercarriage parts for earthmoving equipment, truck parts, and diesel engine components. Further, it holds properties; and provides financial services. Invicta Holdings Limited is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

SacOil Holdings Limited, an independent oil and gas company, engages in the exploration and production of oil and gas properties. It holds interests in exploration and production assets located in Egypt, the Democratic Republic of Congo, Malawi, and Botswana. The company also distributes fuel products, such as diesel, petrol, and paraffin to local and national government, mining, construction, transport, manufacturing, parastatal, reseller, and agricultural clients in South Africa; trades in crude oil in Nigeria; and has a terminal project in Equatorial Guinea. The company was formerly known as SA Mineral Resources Corporation Limited and changed its name to SacOil Holdings Limited in December 2008. SacOil Holdings Limited was incorporated in 1993 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa.

Basil Read Holdings Limited operates as a construction company in South Africa and internationally. It operates through five segments: Construction, Developments, Mining, Roads, and St Helena. The company engages in the civil engineering, road construction, building, mixed-use integrated housing developments, property development, opencast mining, and blasting and excavating. It undertakes civil engineering and building projects, including earthworks, bridges, pipelines, infrastructure, harbor and marine works, industrial plants, sports facilities, roads, highways, and related industrial activities, as well as offers build-operate-transfer contracts, design and construct, and alternative solutions. The company is also involved in the surface contract mining, which includes drill, blast, load, haul, dump, material handling, and processing services to the mining, quarrying, and construction industries. In addition, it provides mine design, infrastructure development, planning, scheduling, operations management, and surveying and optimization services. Further, the company focuses on large-scale mixed income integrated housing developments for government, parastatals, and non-governmental organizations. Additionally, it designs, builds, and operates the St Helena airport project on the island of St Helena. The company was founded in 1952 and is headquartered in Boksburg, South Africa.

Control Instruments Group (Pty) Ltd, through its subsidiaries, manufactures, markets, sells, and supplies branded automotive aftermarket products in South Africa and sub-Saharan Africa. The company primarily offers its services to the replacement parts market for vehicles older than five years, as well as manufactures automotive battery cases for automotive battery brands. It distributes its products through a network of warehouse distributors under the brand names of Gabriel, Autocom, Echlin, VDO, Textar, Mag-Brakes, Warn, Hi-Lift, VisionX, and Truck-Lite. Control Instruments Group (Pty) Ltd also distributes its products to the military, mining, agricultural, and leisure markets. The company was founded in 1948 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa. Control Instruments Group (Pty) Ltd is a subsidiary of Torre Industries Limited.

Datatec Limited provides ICT solutions and services worldwide. The company's Westcon-Comstor segment distributes security, unified communications, networking, and data center products to value added resellers, systems integrators, and service providers. The company's Logicalis segment offers information technology (IT) solutions and managed services comprising IT infrastructure and networking solutions, communications and collaboration, data center, cloud, and managed services to various markets, including financial service, telecommunications, media and technology, education, healthcare, retail, manufacturing, and professional service markets, as well as to the government. Its Corporate, Consulting and Financial Services segment provides strategic, trusted advisory, modeling, and market intelligence services to the telecom, media, and technology industries; and strategic, technical, and operational advisory services to the public and private sectors. The company was founded in 1986 and is based in Sandown, South Africa.

Distell Group Limited, an investment holding company, produces, markets, and distributes alcoholic beverages and other non-alcoholic items in South Africa and internationally. The company offers ciders and ready-to-drinks under the Hunter's, Savanna, Bernini, and Esprit brands; and wines under the 4th Street, Nederburg, Drostdy-Hof, Autumn Harvest Crackling, Original Paarl Perle, J.C. Le Roux, Sedgwick's Old Brown, Two Oceans, Durbanville Hills, Pongracz, Fleur du Cap, Neethlingshof, OBiKWA, Earthbound Wines, Plaisir de Merle, Alto, Allesverloren, Zonnebloem Wines, Cellar Cask, and Autumn Harvest Crackling brands.It also provides spirits primarily under the Amarula, Scottish Leader, Klipdrift, Richelieu, Viceroy, Three Ships Whisky, Oude Meester, Knights Whisky, Bain's Cape Mountain Whisky, Van Ryn's, Black Bottle, Bisquit Cognac, Bunnahabhain, and Deanston Whisky brands. The company was founded in 1925 and is headquartered in Stellenbosch, South Africa. Distell Group Limited is a subsidiary of Remgro-Capevin Investments Proprietary Limited.

Group Five Limited engages in investments and concessions, manufacturing, and engineering and construction in South Africa and internationally. Its investments and concessions business develops, invests in, and operates transport concessions under the Intertoll brand, including toll motorways; develops infrastructure concessions, such as public buildings and power concessions; and invests in and develops commercial, industrial, retail, and residential properties. The company's manufacturing business provides ceiling boards, internal and external cladding boards, fascia boards and embossed building planks, barge boards, and a range of pipe products and building columns for residential and industrial applications; and steel products consisting of reinforcing steel bars, welded building mesh, binding wire and brick force, and large bore spirally welded coated and lined steel pipes. Its engineering and construction business operates as a contractor for building and housing projects; undertakes a range of heavy civil, infrastructure, roads, and earthworks contracts for public and private clients; operates as a contractor for structural, mechanical, electrical instrumentation, and piping projects; offers nuclear construction services; and provides turnkey engineer, procure, and construct (EPC) contracting services. Group Five Limited was founded in 1878 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Jasco Electronics Holdings Limited provides solutions in the areas of telecommunications, information technology, energy, and industry in South Africa and internationally. The company offers contact center solutions; unified communications solutions, including telephony, messaging systems, conferencing, analytics and reporting, and integration; and IT infrastructure solutions, such as data networking, connectivity, intelligent systems, professional, and managed services. It also engages in the design, installation, and maintenance of smart technology solutions for security and fire applications; and provision of smart building solutions covering rooftop management, telecommunications, power, renewable energy, security, fire, IT infrastructure, and building management. In addition, the company offers a range of infrastructure products and services for access, transmission, and operational support systems, and outside plant, as well as rents space on its existing infrastructure to telecommunications operators and service providers; and data center services. Further, it designs, builds, installs, integrates, and maintains video and audio solutions for broadcasters, as well as production and post-production houses; provides power solutions for UPS, generators, transformers, voltage stabilizers, and surge protection and monitoring equipment; and offers photovoltaic energy production solutions, as well as integrated water network management and event management solutions. Additionally, the company manufactures components for plastic injection mouldings and metal pressings, as well as manufactures and assembles wire harness products for the domestic appliance industry; offers paint and print solutions for plastic moulded components; provides electrical plugs, adaptors, and extensions under the Snapper brand; and manufactures salt water chlorination systems. Jasco Electronics Holdings Limited was founded in 1976 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Omnia Holdings Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides specialized chemical products and services used in the agriculture, mining, and chemical sectors in South Africa and internationally. Its Agriculture division produces and trades in granular, liquid, and specialty fertilizers for farmers, co-operatives, and wholesalers; and supplies a range of water-soluble and foliar products, trace elements, and organic soil conditioners. The company's Mining division provides bulk emulsion and blended bulk explosives formulations for the opencast mining industry; produces electronic delay detonators and shocktube initiating systems; manufactures packaged explosives for underground mining and specialized surface blasting operations; offers emulsion explosives products and pumping equipment; and provides value-added services, including Protea Process, a service that covers the design of equipment, logistics, and on-site management. Its Chemicals division manufactures and distributes specialty, functional, and effect chemicals and polymers. This division also manufactures and distributes chemicals, which are used for the treatment of potable water. Omnia Holdings Limited was founded in 1953 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa.

Middle East Diamond Resources Limited engages in the exploration, evaluation, and development of mineral projects primarily in the Bushveld Complex, South Africa. The company primarily holds interest in four platinum group metal project areas, such as Abrina, Klipfontein, Doornpoort, and Syferfontein, as well as a group of seven other project areas; and Syferfontein, an iron ore/vanadium project. It has prospecting rights for platinum group metals across 63000 hectares in the Gauteng, Northwest, and Limpopo provinces of South Africa. The company was formerly known as Sable Metals and Minerals Limited and changed its name to Middle East Diamond Resources Limited in February 2016. Middle East Diamond Resources Limited is based in Sandton, South Africa.

column787: Cnr William Nicol Drive and Peter Place
column791: Italtile Limited operates as a franchisor and retailer of tiles, sanitaryware, bathware, laminated flooring, and other related home-finishing products in South Africa and internationally. The company's product portfolio includes tiles, bathware, and related products, bath and toilet products, showers, cabinets, taps, various related tools, adhesives, tile care products, paints, ceiling decors, hardware products, and accessories. It also invests in properties; and imports and distributes brassware, accessories, tiling tools, laminated floor boards, cabinets, and decors, as well as imports polished and glazed porcelain tiles. As of June 30, 2016, it operated a network of 146 stores in Southern and East Africa under the Italtile Retail, CTM, and TopT brands. The company was founded in 1969 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa. Italtile Limited is a subsidiary of Rallen Proprietary Limited.

KAP Industrial Holdings Limited engages in the supply chain, passenger transport, timber, chemical, automotive components, and bedding businesses in South Africa and internationally. It operates through Diversified Logistics and Diversified Industrial segments. The Diversified Logistics segment provides specialized transport, distribution, warehousing logistics, and supply chain re-engineering services to the mining and infrastructure, manufacturing, industrial, petrochemical, food, agriculture, and allied sectors. This segment also provides transport services to commuter, personnel, intercity, and tourism markets. The Diversified Industrial segment manufactures and distributes sawn timber, poles, wood-based panel products, decorative laminates, and solid surfacing materials; urea formaldehyde and polyethylene terephthalate resins for use in beverages and packaging industries; automotive components; and foam, fabrics, springs, and bases, as well as assembles mattresses. The company is headquartered in Stellenbosch, South Africa. KAP Industrial Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Steinhoff International Holdings Limited.

The company operates approximately 100 hotels MAIA Luxury Resort & Spa, 54 on Bath, Beverly Hills, Palazzo, Sandton Sun, Suncoast Towers, Southern Sun Hotels, Southern Sun Resorts, Paradise Sun, Riverside Sun, Sabi River Sun, Tete Ferry Sun, SunSquare, The Caledon Hotel, Gold Reef City Theme Park Hotel, Garden Court, StayEasy, SUN1, InterContinental Hotels, Crowne Plaza, and Holiday Inn brand names in South Africa, Nigeria, Kenya, Tanzania, Zambia, Mozambique, the United Arab Emirates, and the Seychelles. It also operates 14 casinos and entertainment destinations under the Montecasino, Gold Reef City, Silverstar, The Caledon, Mykonos, Garden Route, Hemingways, Queens, Goldfields, Suncoast, Golden Horse, Blackrock, Emnotweni, and The Ridge names; and approximately 250 conference and banqueting facilities, as well as theatres, cinemas, restaurants, and bars. The company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Fourways, South Africa.

Aspen Pharmacare Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and supplies branded and generic pharmaceutical products, infant nutritionals, and consumer healthcare products. The company offers various branded products for a range of therapeutic categories, including anaesthetics, analgesics, anti-retrovirals, blood and haemopoetic, cardio vascular system, central nervous system, endocrine system, gastro-intestinal tract, infant milk formulations, musculo-skeletal agents, NSAIDs, oncology, oral hygiene, respiratory system, and urinary tract system, as well as ear, nose, and throat. It also provides various generics covering a range of categories, such as anti-depressants; analgesics for pain relief; anti-hypertensives for high blood pressure; bronchodilators for the treatment of asthma; anti-bacterials to treat bacterial infections; anti-gout agents; anti-inflammatory agents; anti-fungal agents; anti-histamines for the treatment of allergies; decongestants; gastro-intestinal agents; dermatologicals; and anti-retrovirals. In addition, the company manufactures narcotic and specialist fine active pharmaceutical ingredients. The company serves pharmacies, retail pharmacy chains, hospitals, clinics, prescribing specialists, dispensing general practitioners, managed healthcare funders, and retail stores across the private and public sectors. It has operations in South Africa, the Asia Pacific, Europe CIS, Latin America, Sub-Saharan Africa, the Middle East, North Africa, the United States, and Canada. Aspen Pharmacare Holdings Limited is based in Durban, South Africa.

Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates private hospitals primarily in South Africa. It operates through two divisions, Hospital and Healthcare Services. The Hospital division provides services to the private medically insured market with general hospital facilities that include intensive care units, high care units, operating theatres, emergency units, maternity units, and cardiac units, as well as other specialized facilities that provide inpatient or outpatient services in the areas of acute rehabilitation, chronic renal dialysis, mental healthcare services, and radiation and chemotherapy oncology. The Healthcare Services division offers acute and long term chronic hospitalization services to state patients; and primary and occupational healthcare services to employer groups in commerce, industry, parastatels, mining, and correctional services. It also provides long term care services to chronically ill, mental health, and frail care patients; and operates district hospital providing acute care to indigent patients, as well as manages customer owned clinics. In addition, this division operates learning college, which offers undergraduate and post graduate diplomas in nursing education, management, and clinical practice; and a foundation that provides financial sponsorship, as well as hospital and nursing services. Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited operates a network of 63 hospitals in Johannesburg, Pretoria, Cape Town, Durban, Port Elizabeth, East London, and Bloemfontein. The company was formerly known as Afrox Healthcare Limited and changed its name to Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited in January 2005. Life Healthcare Group Holdings Limited was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in Illovo, South Africa.

Kagiso Media Limited, through its subsidiaries, operates as a media company in South Africa. It operates in four segments: Broadcasting, Information and Other, New Media, and Content. The Broadcasting segment is involved in radio broadcasting, radio advertising, Internet sales environment, and research and marketing activities. Its radio stations offer audiences to national and local advertisers, who buy largely traditional above-the-line advertising airtime directly from the radio stations. This segment also creates online content for the radio audience. The Information and Other segment publishes and sells information in the areas of law, tax, and accounting in printed and electronic forms to professionals and tertiary students. It also provides legal compliance management services and access to public records through an Internet-based purchasing system. The New Media segment is involved in the creation of digital campaign solutions across various digital channels, including cellular, viral, interactive kiosks, experiential spaces, direct digital, interactive television, CD ROMs, and DVDs; online media buying services; and publishes howzit.msn.co.za, which offers Microsoft's Window Live properties, such as Hotmail and Windows live messenger, as well as offers mobile and video channels. The Content segment produces and distributes audio-visual content on broadcasting platforms, such as live and prerecorded television, concept development, content production, post production, editing, and broadcasting. The company also manages sports rights advertising. Kagiso Media Limited was founded in 1997 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. As of December 11, 2013, Kagiso Media Ltd. was taken private.

column791: Argent Industrial Limited manufactures and trades in steel and steel-related products worldwide. The company operates through four segments: Manufacturing, Steel Trading, Automotive, and Properties. It manufactures rubber mouldings; steel office and industrial furniture products; wrought iron style gates, wooden gates, wrought iron railings, decking panels, gate automation products, fixtures and fittings, posts, security products, and bonfires/wood burners; decorative paint and coating products, industrial paint products, wood and floor coatings, curtain suspensions, castor packs, brushware, aluminum extrusions, and straight edges and trolleys; brick fireplaces; and scrap products. The company also supplies gates and fencing products, metal deck panels, and garden arches; castors and wheels, fibreglass and aluminum ladders, aluminum scaffolding equipment, pallet trucks, storage systems, trolleys, conveyors, and access equipment; vehicle accessories; aluminum products; lifting and rigging equipment; readymix concrete and mortars; steel sheets, plates, coils, flats, angles, tubes, and pipes; hot rolled sheets, galvanized sheets, various steel sections, tubing products, and roof sheeting products; and tools for the office furniture industry. In addition, it retails home and security related products; manufactures and supplies speed control systems; manufactures a range of anti-burglar protection and security products; and supplies balustrades, burglar guards, mezzanine floors and stairs, toilets, storage/stillage boxes, traffic street light poles, carport structures, windows and doors, and wire bending products. Further, the company provides concrete building products; sub-components; pressing, cutting, drilling, punching, bending, polishing, fabricating, welding, rolling, hardening, assembling, sub assembly sizing, beading, upsetting, and end forming services; and rents properties. Argent Industrial Limited was founded in 1972 and is based in La Lucia, South Africa.

Transpaco Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures, recycles, and distributes paper and plastic packaging products primarily in South Africa. It operates through Plastics Products, and Paper and Board Products segments. The company manufactures refuse bags, flexible plastic packaging solutions, recycled pre and post-consumer waste polyethylene, and specialized films; and printed folded cartons and package inserts, as well as spirally wound tubular cardboard cores, carton dividers, void fillers, and angle boards. Its products include black, clear, and color refuse bags, bin liners, and sheeting and films; light, medium, and heavy duty products; retail vest-type plastic bags, retail boutique plastic bags, industrial plastic bags, tubing and sheeting, and scholastic stationery; high and low density polyethylene; and cast pallet stabilization wrappings, stretch films, and layer cast films. The company also provides heavy and light duty cores, yarn and tape cores, conical containers, void fillers, carton dividers, and angle boards; and corrugated boards and cartons, pallet and food wraps, paper bags, tapes and closures, cleaning materials, protective clothing, papers and boards, and packaging machinery. In addition, it distributes packaging products. The company serves retail, industrial, agricultural, mining, pharmaceutical, and automotive sectors. Transpaco Limited is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

AfroCentric Investment Corporation Limited, an investment holding company, provides health administration and health risk management solutions to the healthcare funding industry in South Africa. Its services include, claims processing; client member contact centers; scheme finance management; hospital and medicine benefit management programs; disease management programs; hospital, general practitioner, specialist, optical, and dental networks; negotiations and strategic purchasing of healthcare services on behalf of clients; actuarial and health informatics and analysts; evaluation of technologies, pharmaceuticals, and clinical practices, as well as formulation of clinical health funding policies; and forensic services. The company also offers healthcare management systems for specialized diseases, network connectivity services, and outsourced technology solutions; actuarial prevalence assessment, financial impact analysis, HIV counselling and testing, education and awareness programs, workplace policies and procedures, and corporate treatment programs, as well as knowledge, attitudes, and practice surveys; and treatment for various musculoskeletal disorders, such as back, neck, shoulder, hip, and knee. In addition, it is involved in the provision of pharmacy courier services and services to various medical aid schemes; supply of chronic medication; and operation of information technology platform for clinical information management and pharmaceutical care. AfroCentric Investment Corporation Limited was founded in 2006 and is based in Roodepoort, South Africa.

Bell Equipment Limited manufactures, distributes, and exports various heavy and materials handling equipment primarily for agriculture, forestry, waste handling, construction, and mining and quarrying industries worldwide. The company offers articulated dump trucks (ADT), crawler dozers, dumper trailers, excavators, low profile ADT, motor graders, tractor loader backhoes, and wheeled loaders; and feller bunchers, forwarders, harvesters, loggers, long range forwarders, skidders, timber trucks, and waratah heads. It also provides articulated tractors, cane loaders, cane slew loaders, forklifts, haulage tractors, and tandem trailers; and asphalt construction, earth and sanitary landfill construction, light, stabilization and recycling, and waste management equipment. Further, it provides lubecheck systems, lubricants, simulators, fleet management systems, pre-owned equipment, rebuilt components, and replacement parts; and financing, training, maintenance, and warranty services. The company sells its products primarily through a network of outlets and independent dealers. Bell Equipment Limited was founded in 1954 and is headquartered in Richards Bay, South Africa.

Wilson Bayly Holmes-Ovcon Limited operates as a construction company in South Africa, rest of Africa, and Australia. Its building and construction projects include healthcare and pharmaceutical facilities; special projects; leisure, recreation, and education facilities; concessions and property development; hotels and resorts; office and commercial buildings; residential and retail projects; and golf estates. York Timber Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the commercial forestry, softwood sawmilling, plywood manufacturing, and timber trading businesses in South Africa. Metrofile Holdings Limited provides records management and a range of customer services in South Africa. The company focuses on the various aspects of enterprise records and information management, including archival, storage, retrieval, and destruction of records; conversion of paper and analogue records to digital formats; rotation management and storage of backup media; professional consultancy and records management software; waste paper collection and recycling; and sale and maintenance of document handling equipment, as well as offers business and IT continuity services. It also sells and maintains a range of business equipment, including exam marking systems, library security systems and solutions, scanners, mail handling machines, packaging plants, employee management systems, visitor management software, microfilm solutions, and a range of ICT products, such as dustless keyboards for operating theatres. The company was formerly known as MGX Holdings Limited and changed its name to Metrofile Holdings Limited in February 2005. Metrofile Holdings Limited was founded in 1983 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Sabvest Limited is a private equity and venture capital firm specializing in early venture, mid venture, late venture, emerging growth, growth capital and management buyouts. It seeks to invest equity interests in listed and unlisted companies. It usually invests in companies where key management has meaningful interests or in family managed businesses. The firm does not invest in stage one, start-up or greenfield investments, and turnarounds and is also unlikely to make new investments that exceed 15% of its portfolio or 25% of shareholders' equity. It seeks to invest in companies operating in the information technology, industrial, media, retail, trading, services, financial and distribution industries. The firm seeks to invest in businesses in South Africa, the United Kingdom, and Europe. The firm invests between R5 million ($0.8 million) and R25 million ($4.2 million) in its portfolio companies along with equity stakes between 10% and 40%. It usually invests in companies where key management has meaningful interests or in family managed businesses. The firm may hold majority or joint controlling interests but without direct management responsibility. The firm does not acquire a board seat in case of majority investments and favors large minority stakes in unlisted companies. It may hold equity instruments that are small in percentage terms but where the group is able to exercise influence through board representation or shareholder agreements. The firm also has a secondary investment focus which includes holding cash, bonds, short-term investments, fund participation, shares and other investments and debt instruments. It seeks to hold a meaningful level of investments in international currencies. Sabvest Limited is based in Sandhurst, South Africa.

Unicorn Capital Partners Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a diversified mining company in South Africa. The company operates through five segments: Opencast Mining and Earthmoving, Exploration Drilling, Overburden Drilling and Blasting, Crane Hire, and Coal Mining. Its opencast mining and earthmoving operations include movement and management of various aspects of overburden removal, as well as coal extraction and chrome mining. The company also provides outsourced mining and rehabilitation services; and sells equipment, spares, and anthracite. In addition, it engages in the hiring out of medium to heavy duty mobile cranes with capacities ranging from 25 to 220 tonnes. The company was formerly known as Sentula Mining Limited and changed its name to Unicorn Capital Partners Limited in July 2017. Unicorn Capital Partners Limited was incorporated in 1992 based in Woodmead, South Africa.

The company is also involved in the investment and development of commercial properties; and provision of treasury and debt factoring services, and asset-backed and short-term loans to small and medium-sized businesses, as well as invoice discounting, secured loans, incremental housing finance, specialized finance, and outsourced credit administration for asset finance. Tradehold Limited is based in San Gwann, Malta.

Premium Properties Ltd operates as a property loan stock company in the Republic of South Africa. As of February 28, 2009, the company's property portfolio comprised commercial, retail, industrial, and residential properties with a rentable area of 648,873 square meters, which includes 3,011 residential units. Its property portfolio primarily consists of multi-tenanted buildings located in the Pretoria Central, Hatfield, Silverton, and Johannesburg. Premium Properties Ltd is based in Pretoria, the Republic of South Africa.

Super Group Limited engages in supply chain management, dealerships, and fleet management activities primarily in sub-Saharan Africa, Australia, New Zealand, the United Kingdom, and rest of Europe. The company's Supply Chain division provides supply chain services, including supply chain optimization, consulting, technology, procurement, third party distribution, transport, multi-temperature controlled product distribution, bulk raw material transportation, warehousing, inbound and outbound freight forwarding, customs clearing, import and export consolidation, international airfreight, and bonded cross-border transportation services. This division primarily serves automotive, electronics, hazardous goods, life sciences, pharmaceutical, temperature controlled, and emergency blood and medical service industries. Its Fleet Solutions division offers fleet management solutions for specific transport and vehicle management needs of various customers. This division also provides various value-added services, such as driver, fuel, and tire management; accident and insurance administration; fleet optimization and route planning; vehicle tracking and recovery; and access to its call center services. In addition, it offers a range of leasing and salary packaging solutions to corporate and government customers, as well as heavy commercial fleet management services. The company's Dealerships division operates 54 motor dealerships in South Africa and 15 motor dealerships in the United Kingdom. This division's motor dealerships offer new and used passenger cars and light commercial vehicles, as well as services, parts, finance, and insurance. The company was founded in 1986 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa.

Bauba Platinum Limited engages in the exploration, evaluation, and development of mineral properties in South Africa. The company operates through Chrome Projects and Platinum Exploration segments. It holds interest in the Bauba platinum project comprising eight properties covering an area of approximately 14,390 hectares located in the eastern limb of the Bushveld Igneous Complex; and the Bauba platinum chromite mine lying on the Moeijelijk 412KS farm covering an area of approximately 2,271 hectares located in the northeastern limb of the Bushveld Igneous Complex in the Limpopo province. The company is based in Bryanston, South Africa. Bauba Platinum Limited is a subsidiary of Highland Trading Investments Limited.

Howden Africa Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, designs, manufactures, and markets specialized air and gas handling solutions worldwide. The company operates through Fans and Heat Exchangers, Environmental Control, and Fabrication Technology segments. The Fans and Heat Exchangers segment focuses on air and gas-cooling technologies within the coal/gold mining and power generation markets. This segment offers boiler fans, heat exchangers, site services, HVAC fans, standard and industrial fans and blowers, main surface fans, auxiliary mine fans, and centrifugal blowers. In addition, this segment is also involved in dust extraction on coal mines, mine cooling and heating, ventilation on demand, engineering, and application engineering activities. The Environmental Control segment offers dust extraction and gas-treatment technologies. This segment's products and services include gas cleaning plants, combustion engineering, furnaces, incinerators, process compressors, refrigeration equipment, water chillers, positive displacement blowers, waste water treatment, and control and instrumentation, as well as mine cooling and heating, engineering solutions, and application engineering. The Fabrication Technology division distributes equipment and filler metals for welding and cutting applications. This segment offers air gouging and exothermic cuttings, gas equipment, welding consumables, welding equipment, plasma cutting and torches, welding automation and robotics, and cutting automation products. It serves power generation, petrochemical, mining, construction, refrigeration, water treatment, machinery, fabrication, ship building, and general industries. The company was founded in 1854 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. Howden Africa Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Howden Group South Africa Limited.
