Pick n Pay Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a retailer of food, grocery, and general merchandise. It owns and franchises stores under various formats, including hypermarkets; supermarkets; convenience stores; pharmacies; and liquor, punch, express, hardware, and clothing stores under the Pick n Pay and Boxer names. The company offers various products, such as food, non-edible groceries, clothing, liquor and tobacco, health and beauty products, building and hardware products, and general merchandise. As of February 28, 2016, the company operated 1,410 stores, including 804 company-owned stores and 549 franchise stores; and TM 57 supermarkets. It also provides value-added services, including mobile money, third-party bill payments, gift cards, pre-paid electricity, lotto, and travel and event tickets. The company was founded in 1967 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Eskom Holdings SOC Ltd, together with its subsidiaries, generates, transmits, and distributes electricity to industrial, mining, commercial, agricultural, and residential customers in South Africa. The company operates through Generation, Transmission, Distribution, Energy Purchases/Sales, Group Customer Services, Group Capital, and All Other segments. It generates power through nuclear, hydro, wind, gas turbine, coal, and pumped storage plants. The company also operates a service concession for the generation and transmission of electricity in Uganda. In addition, it sells electricity to redistributors, such as metropolitan and other municipalities who in turn distributes it to businesses and households within their areas of supply; and purchases electricity from independent power producers, as well as buys and sells electricity in the Southern African Development Community region. The company was formerly known as Eskom Holdings Limited and changed its name to Eskom Holdings SOC Ltd in May 2011. Eskom Holdings SOC Ltd was founded in 1923 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Village Main Reef Limited operates as a mining and resources investment company. The company explores for platinum, gold, antimony, and coal deposits. It principally owns the Lesego platinum project situated near Lydenberg, South Africa. The company, formerly known as Village Main Reef Gold Mining Company (1934) Limited, is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. As of May 22, 2015, Village Main Reef Limited was taken private.

column791: Hosken Consolidated Investments Limited, an investment holding company, operates in hotel and leisure, interactive gaming, transport, and mining businesses. It owns and operates hotels and casinos, as well as gaming machines and bingo centers. The company also offers scheduled passenger services through operating 1,073 buses serving 900 routes covering a total area of approximately 2,460 square kilometers; has interests in 3 coal properties; and operates conference and exhibition venues. In addition, it produces and markets wine and brandy; and develops, manufactures, and supplies pressed components for the automotive catalytic converter and OEM markets, as well as provides tubular and exhaust-related components, welding components, poly-V-pulleys, and door lock mechanisms and assemblies. Further, the company provides IT professional services in business analysis and software development; and technology based services and systems for road safety, traffic management, and revenue collection. It has operations in South Africa, Africa, the United Kingdom, and Australia. Hosken Consolidated Investments Limited is based in Zonnebloem, South Africa.

Caxton and CTP Publishers and Printers Limited publishes and prints books, magazines, newspapers, and commercial print primarily in the Republic of South Africa. It is involved in publishing various community newspapers, The Citizen daily newspaper, and other magazines. The company operates online digital platforms, including AutoDealer, DealFinder, Money Web, Look Local, and Property Week, as well as a community news; and provides digital, as well as sales, advertising, and marketing services. It also offers printed packaging solutions, such as litho printed folding cartons, gravure printed cigarette packs and display cartons, litho and gravure printed wet glue, and pressure sensitive labels for the beer and beverage industries, as well as various forms of flexible packaging and specialized printing solutions for the point of sale and entertainment industries. In addition, the company manufactures, imports, and markets printing inks, as well as exports newspaper inks to Tanzania and Uganda; and provides digital, gravure, sheet-fed offset, and web offset printing services. Further, it manufactures and distributes stationery products; replicates and distributes CDs and DVDs; provides repro design services; owns properties; and distributes magazines. Caxton and CTP Publishers and Printers Limited was founded in 1980 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, the Republic of South Africa.

Aveng Limited, together with its subsidiaries, primary engages in the construction and engineering, mining, and steel business worldwide. The company operates through Construction and Engineering, Mining, and Manufacturing and Processing segments. It offers a range of integrated services that cover building, civil engineering, roads, earthworks, concrete, ground engineering, mechanical, piping, electrical, and instrumentation contracting. The company also operates as an engineering, construction, building, and maintenance contractor for the building, infrastructure, and resource markets focusing on building, rail, civil, electrical, marine, mechanical pipelines, fabrication, tunneling, and underground services. In addition, it provides mining services in the areas of shaft sinking, underground development and contract mining, opencast mining, mineral processing, acid mine drainage plants, construction of mining related infrastructure, and supply of mining equipment and products. Further, the company manufactures and supplies concrete products to the construction sector; services and engineered solutions to mining, water, oil and gas, and construction clients; and rail construction and maintenance services to the transport sector, as well as supplies various products and services to the construction, mining, and automotive industries. Aveng Limited is based in Boksburg, South Africa.

Gijima Group Limited provides information and communications technology (ICT) services in southern Africa and internationally. It offers cloud computing services, mobility infrastructure services, occupational hygiene and environmental services, distributed computing services that provide end-user support for desktops and associated services, electronic signatures solutions, analytic laboratory services, Web analytics services, SAP solutions, enterprise SEO solutions, and oracle services. It also provides recruitment, selection, assessment, and placement services for ICT candidates in the mining, manufacturing, financial, and public sectors; designs and develops custom e-learning programs; and offers business process outsource services, such as response handling and outsourced recruitment, and administration and payroll services. It serves mining, manufacturing, telecommunications, financial services, retail and hospitality, public sector, and other industries. Gijima Group Limited is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa.

Comair Limited provides scheduled and non-scheduled airline services in South Africa, sub-Saharan Africa, and the Indian Ocean Islands. It operates through two segments, Airline and Non-airline. DigiCore Holdings Limited designs, researches, develops, manufactures, sells, and supports GPS/GSM fleet management and vehicle tracking solutions primarily in South Africa and internationally. It provides various vehicle tracking solutions, including Ctrack Insure, a monitoring and tracking system that offers proactive alerts in the event of battery or tracking-unit tamper or border approach; Ctrack Insure Protector for tracking and monitoring with smart collision and security; Ctrack Secure, which provides Internet-enabled access to view vehicle movements; and Ctrack Secure Protector, a satellite vehicle tracking solution. The company also provides fleet management solutions, such as Ctrack Lite, an entry level vehicle tracking and fleet management system providing driver behavior information and full status reports, such as over speeding, harsh braking, and excessive idling; Ctrack Assist for the tracking and management of light commercial, sales, FML, car rental, and security vehicles, as well as trailer fleets; OBDII Fuel Reader, which provides fuel economy data assisting small and large fleet operators to manage fuel related costs; Ctrack Solo, a mobile solution for the tracking and management of the professional hauler, logistics and supply chain management, mobile workforce management, public transport, and emergency services applications; Ctrack On-the-Road, an onboard system that helps fleet operators in saving time and money through advanced navigation, task management, messaging, optimal routing, voice functionality, and driver behavior; and Ctrack Multi-comms. In addition, it offers Ctrack Wireless, a re-deployable tracking system. The company provides its products for private vehicles and small fleet, medium to large fleet, heavy duty, and transport, as well as asset tracking, monitoring, and revenue management. DigiCore Holdings Limited was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa.

Astrapak Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and distributes various plastic packaging products primarily in South Africa. column791: Ecsponent Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in capital raising, asset management, enterprise/SME funding, collections, and private equity businesses in South Africa, Botswana, Zambia, Namibia, and Swaziland. PSV Holdings Ltd provides steel, stainless steel, industrial supplies, specialised control valves, engineering linings, cryogenic equipment, storage tanks, and technology to the mining, water, waste water management, health care, infrastructure, and manufacturing sectors.  The company operates through two segments, Industrial Supplies and Specialised Services. The Industrial Supplies segment purchases and distributes general industrial and automotive supplies; supplies steel, piping, industrial tools, consumable supplies, and automotive capital equipment to mining and industrial clients; offers bespoke and turnkey solutions to companies in need of computerized vehicle testing stations and general workshop equipment; and provides consultancy services on workshop requirements, as well as offers one-stop solution for mining projects. The Specialised Services segment is involved in the manufacture and supply of gas and cryogenic equipment, including road tankers and cryogenic storage vessels to gas and chemical industries; supply of geosynthetic and plastic lining solutions to assist mining operators for the purpose of seepage containment, corrosion, and environmental protection; and the provision of repair and refurbishment services. PSV Holdings Limited is based in Greenstone Hill, South Africa.

CompuClearing Outsourcing Limited is an investment holding company and through its subsidiaries, provides information technology products and services to the customs clearing, freight forwarding, air cargo, supply chain, and logistics related industries in South Africa. The company operates through three segments: Software Rental, Hardware Rental, and Cargowise One. The company's solutions include cClearing, an application for multimodal imports and exports, cross border clearances, customs, cargo dues, bonded warehousing, refund claims, permits, and landed costing; CargoWise One, a custom-designed system for logistics service providers; cTariff, a customs tariff solution in online and paper formats; cLogistics, a logistics management solution for various freight forwarding requirements; and cAccounting, a financial package for various transactions, such as invoicing, accounts receivables, cash books, disbursement reconciliation, accounts payables, general ledger, and customer management. Its solutions also comprise cFly, an integrated airline and airport ground handler system for the management and control of bookings, handling, billing, and tracking of air shipments; cFile, an online document management system to capture, store, and retrieve documents; and cReporting to create, save, and share reports. In addition, the company offers support services consisting of call centre/helpdesk, as well as customer relations representatives; develops and integrates solutions to its clients; and provides classroom training to customers and non-customers. Further, it offers cCloud, a platform that offers data, data management, and data storage services; and cEnquiries for airfreight and sea freight container tracking, generic track and trace, air waybill image enquiry, and bill of entry enquiry. The company was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

CompuClearing Outsourcing Limited is an investment holding company and through its subsidiaries, provides information technology products and services to the customs clearing, freight forwarding, air cargo, supply chain, and logistics related industries in South Africa. The company operates through three segments: Software Rental, Hardware Rental, and Cargowise One. The company's solutions include cClearing, an application for multimodal imports and exports, cross border clearances, customs, cargo dues, bonded warehousing, refund claims, permits, and landed costing; CargoWise One, a custom-designed system for logistics service providers; cTariff, a customs tariff solution in online and paper formats; cLogistics, a logistics management solution for various freight forwarding requirements; and cAccounting, a financial package for various transactions, such as invoicing, accounts receivables, cash books, disbursement reconciliation, accounts payables, general ledger, and customer management. Its solutions also comprise cFly, an integrated airline and airport ground handler system for the management and control of bookings, handling, billing, and tracking of air shipments; cFile, an online document management system to capture, store, and retrieve documents; and cReporting to create, save, and share reports. In addition, the company offers support services consisting of call centre/helpdesk, as well as customer relations representatives; develops and integrates solutions to its clients; and provides classroom training to customers and non-customers. Further, it offers cCloud, a platform that offers data, data management, and data storage services; and cEnquiries for airfreight and sea freight container tracking, generic track and trace, air waybill image enquiry, and bill of entry enquiry. The company was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Traxys Africa Holdings trades in ferrous and non-ferrous metals and minerals, carbon, plastic raw materials, rubber, and chemical products in South Africa and internationally. It operates in two segments, Trading Activities and Investment Activities. The Trading Activities segment trades in ferroalloys, including ferromanganese, silico manganese, ferrochrome, and stainless steel alloys; non-ferrous metals comprising aluminum, copper, lead, tin, zinc, and titanium; ores, such as manganese ores, iron ores, and chrome ores; chemicals and food additives; and plastics consisting of PP, HDPE, PVC, PET, calcium carbonate fillers, and masterbatches. This segment also trades in carbons, including anthracite, char, coal, charcoal, and metallurgical coke; and minor metals consisting of tantalum, tungsten, magnesium, cobalt, and vanadium. The Investment Activities segment invests in equity; and provides project loan funding in mining and logistics projects in order to secure product off-take and logistics infrastructure. The company was formerly known as Metmar Limited and changed its name to Traxys Africa Holdings in October 2015. Traxys Africa Holdings was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Bryanston, South Africa.

Verimark Holdings Limited operates as a retail company that sources, develops, and distributes various products in the housewares, exercise and fitness, health and beauty, DIY, automotive, educational toys, and personal comfort categories in South Africa and internationally. The company offers houseware products comprising slicers and choppers; blade sharpeners, power peelers, rolling knives, and kitchen tools; houseware solutions; and cooking products, as well as accessories and general houseware products. It also provides health and beauty products that include appliances and beauty products; cookware products, such as combos and sets, pans, and lids; and cleaning products comprising mops and brooms, microfiber cloths, replacements, accessories, window mates, and detergents, as well as cleaning solutions. In addition, the company offers DIY products, which include sealants, garden hoses, motion sensor lights, screwdrivers, and blade sharpeners, as well as pool surface skimming systems and replacement bags, and renovator sets and spanners; car care products; educational toys, game stations, and other toys; and fitness products, such as home work out and ab sculpting systems. It primarily distributes cookware and kitchenware products under the Bauer, Bastille, Twista, and Shogun; home cleaning products under the Genesis, Floorwiz, and Microwiz; health and fitness products under the Maxxus, Orbitrek, and V-ssage; DIY and automotive products under the Diamond Guard, Prolong, Durablade, Pool Gobbler, and Gorilla; and beauty products under the Perfect Curl, Pink Armor, and Genie Bra brands, as well as educational and fun toys under the i-Play brand. The company sells its products through approximately 1,401 retail partner stores, as well as 77 owned and franchised stores under the As Seen on TV name; and through online. Verimark Holdings Limited was founded in 1977 and is headquartered in Randburg, South Africa.

Iliad Africa Limited engages in the sourcing, retailing, and redistribution of building materials in South Africa. It operates in two segments, General Building Materials and Specialised Building Materials. The General Building Materials segment provides a range of hardware products and building materials. This segment operates through 24 stores of Inland subdivision and 22 stores of Coastal subdivision. The Specialised Building Materials segment offers various differentiated building products primarily consisting of imported goods. It provides plumbing and hardware, boards, and ironmongery clusters, as well as offers equipment for hire. This segment operates through 12 retail outlets and 16 wholesale outlets. The company offers its products under the Suncol, Buchel, Design Hardware, Bildware, BUCO, Saflok, W&B Hardware, Cachet, Chipbase, Citiwood, and B-One brands. It markets its products to large-scale developers and contractors, homeowners, and do-it-yourself enthusiasts. Iliad Africa Limited is based in Midrand, South Africa. As of January 12, 2016, Iliad Africa Ltd. operates as a subsidiary of Steinhoff International Holdings N.V.

column791: Indequity Group Limited provides short-term insurance products to professional and affluent private client markets in South Africa. Adapt IT Holdings Limited provides specialized information technology (IT) services and solutions. The company's Education segment provides turnkey enterprise resource planning (ERP) product, ITS integrator, and services to the higher education sector. Its Manufacturing segment offers tranquility ERP; safety health environment and quality solutions; SAP human capital management cloud services; and telecommunications business intelligence solutions. The company's Financial Services segment provides business intelligence solutions and services to the financial services sector. Its Energy segment offers consulting and software solutions and services to oil and gas, power, renewable, and other energy sectors. The company also provides software services in the areas of business and technical advisory, cloud computing, development and integration, recruitment, and training and development, as well as offers application development services. It serves the mining and manufacturing, education, financial services, and energy sectors in approximately 38 countries worldwide. Adapt IT Holdings Limited has partnerships with IBM, Microsoft, Oracle, and SAP. The company is headquartered in Durban, South Africa.

column787: Corner Bram Fischer Drive and Will Scarlet Road
column791: Cognition Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, provides interactive telecommunication, switching, and business services primarily in South Africa. The company operates through two segments, Active Data Exchange Services, and Knowledge Creation and Management. The company's active data exchange services include short message, interactive voice response, Vmail one-on-one marketing, mobi site, fulfillment, call center, and bespoke services, as well as unstructured supplementary service data, instant messaging, email, fax2email, and email2fax services. Its active data exchange services also comprise advertising, promotion, direct marketing, and CRM services. In addition, the company provides Knowledge 350, a 15 step business process, which creates an integrated and logical process that assists companies to build databases and to move from segmenting customers to single customer profiles with detailed demographics and psychographics. Further, it offers MyPoint, a managed community service, which enables panelists to complete surveys and reward them with points, prizes, and benefits; Community Builds, an interactive relationship-building program; qualitative and quantitative market research services; and omnibus/syndicated studies. Additionally, the company provides Web design, development, and hosting services, as well as associated search engine optimization input services; and annual quantifications, reports tracking, in-store observation, and liquor in-store pricing, as well as print ad tracking, and commissioned and consumer research services. It serves apparel, automotive, consumer packaged goods, financial, food services, information technology and communication, manufacturing, packaging, raw materials, retail, and wholesale sectors and industries. The company was formerly known as FoneWorx Holdings Limited and changed its name to Cognition Holdings Limited in January 2015. Cognition Holdings Limited is headquartered in Randburg, South Africa.

MICROmega Holdings Limited provides information technology, financial, and support services in South Africa. It offers occupational health, safety, and environmental risk management services; and contractual manpower, recruitment, HR and industrial relations management, payroll bureau, project logistics, and employee benefits for mining, engineering, construction, offshore oil and gas, petrochemical, power generation, and agriculture sectors. The company also provides intermediary broking services in the areas of foreign exchange, OTC derivatives, fixed income securities, repurchase agreements, and money market instruments to commercial and investment banks, stock brokers, and trading entities. In addition, it offers integrated technology solutions, enterprise management systems, and multidisciplinary professional services, including accounting, auditing, and risk management; corporate and municipal finance; change and HR management; engineering; information communication technology infrastructure design, configuration, implementation, and maintenance; software and systems development; administration; project management; organizational restructuring; and strategic planning to municipalities, public entities, government, and private sector. Further, the company offers plastic water meters, ball valves, and meter boxes; pre-payment water meters and electronic water control devices; and consulting services. Additionally, it provides multi-protocol label switching networks, hosting facilities, Internet, and cloud computing services; Set-it, a system to design, integrate, and manage organizational strategy; iConnect, a wireless alarming solution; Whatsup plug and play solution; Coretalk, a SMS communication service; and PROMU accounting package. It also provides chemical analytical services that focus on chemical analysis of food, fish, and beverage products. The company is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. The company is a subsidiary of Friedshelf 1382 (Pty) Ltd.

Massmart Holdings Limited operates as a retail and wholesale distributor. It operates through four segment: Massdiscounters, Masswarehouse, Massbuild, and Masscash. The Massdiscounters segment operates discount retail stores that offer general merchandise, fresh food, groceries, liquor, and footwear, as well as technological solutions in multimedia and hi-tech under the Game and DionWired retail formats. This segment operates 165 stores in South Africa, Botswana, Ghana, Kenya, Lesotho, Malawi, Mozambique, Namibia, Nigeria, Tanzania, Uganda, and Zambia. The Masswarehouse segment operates warehouse stores under the Makro and The Fruitspot names that sell food, liquor, and general merchandise for personal, commercial, and trading customers; and fresh and cut fruit and vegetables. This segment operates 20 stores in South Africa. The Massbuild segment operates DIY, home improvement, and building materials stores under the Builders Warehouse, Builders Express, Builders Superstore, and Builders Trade Depot brands. This segment operates 104 stores in South Africa, Botswana, Mozambique, and Zambia. The Masscash segment engages in the wholesale of food, liquor, cosmetics, toiletries, and haircare products under the CBW and Trident, Jumbo, and Shield brands; and operation of retail outlets under Cambridge Food and Rhino brands. This segment operates 123 stores South Africa, Botswana, Lesotho, Mozambique, Namibia, and Swaziland. Massmart Holdings Limited was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. Massmart Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Main Street 830 (Pty) Ltd.

Mercantile Bank Holdings Limited, a bank-controlling and investment holding company, provides banking and financial services to the business, commercial, and alliance banking markets in South Africa. The company's deposit products include call accounts, notice deposits, fixed deposits, money market accounts, and business savings accounts; and lending products comprise overdrafts, term loans, asset finance, and commercial property finance. It also provides debit cards, credit cards, drive cards, and electronic banking services; travel insurance, and short and long-term insurance solutions; and cash and merchant services. In addition, the company offers spot market services, foreign exchange contracts, and derivatives, as well as traveller's cheque and foreign cash services; money market solutions, including call accounts, term deposits, and structured solutions; and trade finance products, such as letters of credit, trade guarantees, bills for collection, and exchange control and SWIFT products, as well as private banking services. Further, it is involved in securitization, property holding, and rental finance activities. The company was founded in 1965 and is headquartered in Sandown, South Africa. Mercantile Bank Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Caixa Geral de Depositos S.A.

Santova Limited provides international logistics solutions primarily in Africa, the Asia Pacific, the United Kingdom, and Europe. The company offers supply chain solutions; international insurance products; marine insurance products, such as cargo, transit cover, stock throughputs, and strikes and war risks insurance products; general insurance products consisting of business and personal assets, indemnity, motor, liability, specialized, financial, and engineering and construction cover insurance products; and client sourcing and procurement management solutions. It also provides statutory solutions, such as customs and excise clearing and consultation, disbursement funding, bonded warehousing and in-bond transit management, and maritime law consultancy solutions; transit solutions comprising international freight forwarding, express courier services, intermodal transport, and vessel chartering; warehousing and distribution solutions, including storage, pick and pack, kitting, transport planning, and transport management; project and specialized out of gauge cargo management; and value added services consisting of product quality inspections, port supervision and wharf inspection services, price tagging, packaging and labelling, groupage, and consolidation and deconsolidation services. In addition, the company offers information technology solutions for supply chain. Santova Limited is headquartered in Durban, South Africa.

Moneyweb Holdings Limited, an integrated media company, engages in the digital, broadcast, and print publishing fields in the Republic of South Africa. OneLogix Group Limited provides logistics and related services in South Africa. The company operates through Abnormal Logistics and Primary Products Logistics segments. It offers vehicle delivery services through a fleet of approximately 300 trucks and specialized car carrying trailers; new commercial vehicle delivery services; and project logistics and abnormal load solutions, including scheduling and executing harbor movements, and warehousing and management of staged and aggregate moves with monitoring and reporting services. The company also provides liquid transport services for agricultural, chemical, foodgrade, cryogenic, or liquid petroleum gas products through a fleet of approximately 160 tankers; cross-border movement services for general freight and commodities; refrigerated logistics services for chilled, fruit, and vegetable markets; and transportation services for agricultural inputs, such as fertilizer, as well as the final agricultural products. In addition, it provides accident repairs, structural repairs to chassis, cab rebuilds, specialized spray painting, and accident recovery services for commercial trucks; warehouse handling and storage services; specialized transport related accounting software solutions; and integrated driver management solutions. OneLogix Group Limited was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in Kempton Park, South Africa.

Primeserv Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides human capital solutions in the Republic of South Africa. The company operates in two segments, Staffing and Recruitment Services, and Training and Consulting Services. It offers human resources (HR) solutions, such as business and HR strategy and structure workshops, HR balanced scorecards, business and job profiles or internal capacity building, integrated functional/divisional and/or job profiles development, competency and psychometric assessment, learning and development strategy development, skills audits and/or training needs analysis, learning and development interventions implementation, ETQA processes, and learning materials design and development. The company's HR solutions also comprise performance management audits, methodology workshops, policies and procedures, and training; measurement tools development; job evaluation/grading; remuneration and reward systems and processes; salary surveys; HR policies and procedures; climate surveys; IR consulting and training; occupational health and safety consulting and training; and BEE consulting support services. In addition, it provides flexible staffing, permanent staff resourcing, payroll and wage bureau, corporate and technical training, learnership, specialist recruitment, and talent management services, as well as employee lifestyle benefit related products. The company serves logistics, warehousing and distribution, wholesale and retail, manufacturing and engineering, and construction sectors. Primeserv Group Limited was founded in 1997 and is based in Illovo, the Republic of South Africa.

African Equity Empowerment Investments Limited formerly known as Sekunjalo Investments Limited is a private equity firm specializing in acquisitions, PIPEs, and buyouts. It seeks to invest in companies operating in the food, fishing, marine, biotherapeutics , healthcare, pharmaceuticals, information technology, telecommunication, Mobile solutions, solar energy, financial services, aquaculture, biotechnology, enterprise development, events management including entertainment, and travel sectors. The firm prefers to invest companies based in South Africa. It is open to acquiring non-controlling stakes. The firm invests using its balance sheet and personal capital. African Equity Empowerment Investments Limited was founded in May 1996 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Spur Corporation Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a restaurant franchisor in South Africa and internationally. The company operates and franchises sit-down family restaurants under the Spur Steak Ranches, including Spur Grill & Go, as well as Panarottis Pizza Pasta, and John Dory's Fish Grill Sushi brands; quick-service takeaways under the Captain DoRegos brand; steakhouses under the The Hussar Grill brand; Italian pizza and pasta restaurants under the Casa Bella brand; and gourmet burgers, ribs, and wings restaurants under the RocoMamas brand. Stella Vista Technologies Limited designs, produces, integrates, sells, rents, and supports communication and information systems. It designs multi-media mass communications systems, as well as provides displays, control equipments, and software. The company's line of multi-purpose products include scoreboards, video display screens, electronic perimeter boards, flight information display boards, and combined text and graphic messaging displays primarily under the Titan and LB Series brands. It serves sports, business, entertainment, and transportation markets primarily in South Africa, the Middle East, the Indian sub-continent, the Caribbean, the United Kingdom, and Ireland. The company was formerly known as Stardust Electronics and changed its name to Stella Vista Technologies Limited in June 1999. Stella Vista Technologies Limited was founded in 1994 and is headquartered in Kyalami, South Africa.

SilverBridge Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides business solutions to the financial services industry. It operates through Implementation Services, Support services, Hosting and outsourcing Services, Software Rental, and Research and Development segments. The company's product include ExergyLife, a policy administration system for the life insurance companies; ExergyGroups, a group scheme administration system; and Snapper, a Microsoft Word style user interface that allows the creation of standard letters. It also offers, rents, and leases Eco-Suite, an end-to-end solution for life assurance, pension, and group administration. In addition, the company provides hosting, technical outsourcing, and business process outsourcing services; actuarial consulting, including fraud investigations, product development, pricing and ratings, enterprise risk management, corporate planning, and others; and business intelligence solutions comprising valuation extracts, basic business indicators, and business intelligence solutions, as well as data analytics services. SilverBridge Holdings Limited offers its products in the Republic of South Africa, as well as in other African countries, including Swaziland, Zimbabwe, Namibia, Lesotho, Kenya, Angola, Botswana, Malawi, Mauritius, and Ghana. The company was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Pretoria, the Republic of South Africa.

Amalgamated Electronic Corporation Limited, through its subsidiaries, designs, manufactures, and supplies electronic equipment, technologies, and solutions to the security and power supply industries in South Africa and internationally. The company operates data network comprising base stations and repeater technology for the wireless transmission of data across secure network channels. It also designs radio and GSM transmitters, receivers, and transceivers used primarily in the security industry and related niche markets; and a range of related electronic security products, which include security personnel monitoring units, vehicle dispatchers, long and short range remote controllers, and electronic gate opening technology. In addition, the company is involved in the property investment business; and provision of financial and administration services, as well as installs, manages, and maintains various equipment and licenses used on radio and GSM Independent Communications Authority of South Africa frequencies. Amalgamated Electronic Corporation Limited is based in Florida, South Africa. As of October 21, 2016, Amalgamated Electronics Corporation Limited was taken private.

Value Group Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides supply chain solutions in South Africa. It operates through General Distribution, Truck Rental and Other, and Retail Logistics segments. The company offers distribution services, including express courier, breakbulk, retail delivery, DC delivery, front door delivery, home delivery, dangerous goods, overborder, crossborder, reverse logistics, IT integration, and security services; and warehousing services, such as dedicated, multi-principal, transshipment, bonded, dangerous goods, managed solution, and value added services. It is also involved in the fleet management, forklift and commercial vehicle rental and leasing, and clearing and forwarding activities; and warehousing, distribution, and wholesale of various fast moving consumer goods to the convenience, formal, and informal sectors, which primarily includes independent traders, fuel forecourts, and small retailers. In addition, the company offers import and export services, such as international courier, container haulage, intermodal, overborder, and crossborder services; and materials handling services that include rentals, FMLs, outright purchases, repairs and maintenance, spares accessories, and tires. Further, it provides truck rental, refrigerated fleet, film fleet, mine spec, FML, linehaul, and dedicated distribution services; and truck, trailer, and forklift repairs and maintenance services, as well as panel beating and branding services. The company offers its break-bulk and single party distribution and warehousing services to a range of customers in the automotive, electronics, chemical, textile, packaging, mining, construction, telecommunications, and pharmaceutical industries. Value Group Limited was founded in 1981 and is headquartered in Isando, South Africa.

Stellar Capital Partners Limited is no longer investing. It is a principal investment firm specializing in investments in a portfolio of equity, debt and hybrid securities, in listed and unlisted businesses, unconstrained by any particular market or sector. The firm also seeks to invest in growth and early-maturity stage businesses in which management teams remain equity incentivised throughout the investment life cycle. It prefers to invest in financial services, technology sector, industrials and support services, financials and disruptive opportunities across all markets. The firm seeks to invest in companies based in South Africa with focused international operations with the ability to over time invest in foreign based investments also. It prefers to take strategic or controlling interests in its portfolio companies, establishing primarily large minority equity holdings, but retain the ability to hold majority holdings, particularly during the initial stage of the investment. The firm seeks board representation within its investees' reporting structures without establishing board control for prolonged periods of the investment cycle. The firm prefers not to retain operational management of its investees for prolonged periods, but will hold the ability do so during the initial stage of the investment or as is deemed necessary. The firm seeks to opportunistically utilise its balance sheet to generate fees for shareholders through corporate finance strategies in support of investee companies or on a standalone basis. It was formerly known as ConvergeNet Holdings Limited. Stellar Capital Partners Limited was founded in 2005 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa with an additional office in Centurion, South Africa.

Astral Foods Limited operates as an integrated poultry producer in South Africa and internationally. It operates through three segments: Poultry, Feed, and Other Africa. The company manufactures animal feeds and broiler genetics; produces and sells day-old broiler chicks and hatching eggs; manufactures and markets vitamin and mineral pre-mixes for use in animal feeds; and offers a range of feed additives, and commodity and specialty raw materials. It is also involved in the integrated breeder and broiler production operations; operation of abattoirs; processing operations; and sale and distribution of various poultry brands. In addition, the company retails animal health products; and provides laboratory analytical services to the animal feed industry. The company offers its products under the Ross 308, Meadow, Provimi, National Chicks, CAL, Goldi, County Fair, Festive, Mountain Valley, SupaStar, TigerChicks, Tiger Animal Feeds, Mozpintos, and National Chicks Swaziland brands. Astral Foods Limited is based in Centurion, South Africa.

Phumelela Gaming and Leisure Limited operates as a horseracing and totalizator betting company in South Africa and internationally. It operates and manages 4 racecourses, 5 training centers, approximately 200 tote outlets, a telephone-betting center, and an online tote betting site. The company also operates Tellytrack, a horseracing television channel that broadcasts live horseracing audio, visual, and data to retail outlets and home viewers. In addition, it produces various horseracing publications, including Computaform, a horseracing form guide; Racing Express, a horseracing insert that appears in daily newspaper; and Computaform Express, a multi-meeting horseracing form guide, as well as operates horseracing venue as a banqueting and conferencing venue. Further, it offers sports betting services through various channels, including a range of tote bets; and engages in property holding activities. The company was founded in 1997 and is based in Turffontein, South Africa.

Investec Bank Limited, as a specialist bank, focuses on investment, corporate and institutional banking, and private banking activities in Southern Africa. The company accepts private bank accounts, private business accounts, fixed deposits, instant access accounts, and flexible notice accounts. Its financing and lending products include motor vehicle finance, home and personal loans, asset finance, specialized and structured finance, property development finance, aviation finance, commercial property finance, corporate lending, asset finance, growth and acquisition finance, medical practice finance, power and infrastructure finance, and specialized finance. The company also offers investing solutions, such as portfolio and asset management services, wealth management, online stockbroking, retirement, and advisory stockbroking services; structured products; property funds; institutional solutions; and charities and trusts, business cash, and deposits and cash management solutions, as well as redeemable preference shares. In addition, it provides foreign exchange services; equity services, including forex, interest rate, money market, commodity, equities structuring, and institutional equity trading services; and advisory services. Further, the company offers property development, acquisitions, and fund management services; and medical banking, young professional banking, and online banking services. It serves corporates, government, and institutional clients, as well as high net worth individuals, entrepreneurs, high-income professionals, self-employed entrepreneurs, owner managers in mid-market companies, and investors. The company was founded in 1974 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. Investec Bank Limited is a subsidiary of Investec Limited.

Nedbank Limited provides various banking and financial services to various customers. The company accepts various deposit products, including current accounts, savings accounts, call and notice deposits, fixed deposits, negotiable certificates of deposits, term deposits, and cash management deposits, as well as investment accounts. It also provides credit cards; home, vehicle, student, and personal loans; overdrafts; financial planning services; and foreign exchange services. In addition, the company offers assets, life, income and credit protection, and funeral insurance; and general business, specialized, general liability, business overheads, business owner, and key person insurance, as well as direct business cover, investment services, and capital guarantees. Further, it provides a mix of listed offshore equity portfolios; investment plans; portfolio management services; corporate finance, stock broking, trading, debt advisory, and management services; start-up, business growth, and short term loans, as well as structured, property finance, and asset finance solutions; financial assistance and debtor management solutions; and aircraft, carbon, export credit, global commodity, leveraged, mining, oil and gas, private equity, property, public sector, infrastructure, energy, and telecomm finance, as well as corporate lending and advances. Additionally, the company offers payment and receipts, documentary credits and collections, guarantees, trade finance, customer foreign currency accounts, and treasury services; cash management, electronic banking, trade, and custodial services; and merchant payment and support solutions. It operates in South Africa, other African countries, Europe, Asia, the United States, and internationally. The company is headquartered in Sandton, South Africa. Nedbank Limited is a subsidiary of Nedbank Group Ltd.

Business Connexion Group Limited, an investment holding company, operates as an integrator of business solutions based on information and communications technology primarily in South Africa. Lewis Group Limited, a credit retailer, sells household furniture and electrical appliances in South Africa, Botswana, Lesotho, Swaziland, and Namibia. Esor Limited operates as a civil engineering and construction company in principally South Africa and Zimbabwe. The company operates in two segments, Esor Construction and Esor Developments. It engages in the roads, township infrastructures, water and sewerage reticulation projects, and concrete projects construction, as well as the construction and rehabilitation of onshore pipelines. The company also undertakes building and housing projects, including office, retail, leisure, residential, mining, governmental, and infrastructure projects, as well as undertakes low-income housing projects in bonded and social rental, gap, FLISP, and RDP/BNG markets. In addition, it undertakes environmental and safety, pipeline installation, lining and coating, earthworks, structures, testing and pigging, and valves and other special works; and provides pipe services, such as bridge jacking, culvert jacking, pipejacking, shaft sinking, and slabjacking. Further, the company offers sanitation services, including water and sanitation implementation, bulk water and sewer infrastructure construction, containerized ablution facilities installation, brick and mortar ablution blocks construction, modular ablution facilities construction, septic tank and soak-away pits construction, social facilitation and education. Additionally, it engages in property investment and development activities. The company was formerly known as Esorfranki Limited and changed its name to Esor Limited in December 2013. Esor Limited was founded in 1946 and is based in Germiston, South Africa. As of February 24, 2017, Esor Limited operates as a subsidiary of Geomer Investments Proprietary Limited.

JSE Limited operates as a securities exchange in South Africa. The company provides trading in equities, warrants, and exchange-traded products; equity and equity-related futures and options; agricultural grain products and cash-settled derivatives on various commodities, including softs, energy, and various metals; interest rate products; and currency futures and options. It also provides clearing and settlement services; primary market, secondary market, post-trade, and technology services; and information services, including market data, as well as sells live, statistical, historical, and end-of-day data. The company was founded in 1887 and is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Morvest Group Limited provides business support services, information communication and technology solutions, and retail and consumer services to public and private sectors in South Africa and internationally. The company provides professional services, including due diligence, business continuity planning, business performance improvement, and organizational restructuring services; business and software solutions through management and transformation consulting, technology and integration, and strategy realization services; financial services; governance services; human capital management services, such as contracting, permanent staffing, executive search, response handling, verification, company specific account management, advertising and recruitment campaigning, and project/services based resourcing services; and training services. It also offers outsourcing solutions, which include packaging and mass customization for SIMs, CDs, DVDs, loyalty cards, and scratch cards; and secure print solutions and consumable supplies. In addition, the company provides business application solutions to connect businesses to the ecosystem of partners, customers, suppliers, employees, and regulatory agencies; consumer mobile solutions that offer delivery, implementation, and support services for mobile broadband and GSM convergence technologies to mobile operators; information intelligence solutions; and infrastructure services. Further, it offers short-term insurance, risk solutions, asset management, private equity, forex, and personal income tax services; travel and event management, and exclusive concierge services; and e-commerce retail solutions, as well as invest in retail, commercial, and residential properties. The company was formerly known as Morvest Business Group Limited and changed its name to Morvest Group Limited in January 2015. Morvest Group Limited is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Absa Bank Limited provides various banking products and services primarily in South Africa and Namibia. The company accepts cheque, youth, transactional, and business accounts. Its loan products include personal, express, instant, home, car, study, structured, short and medium term, and trade and working capital loans; vehicle and asset, property, and debt finance; and overdraft and revolving credit facilities. The company also offers credit and debit cards; savings and investment products; home, car, household, life and funeral, travel, will, trust, estate, personal asset risk, and business insurance products; and youth and student, Islamic and international banking, investment management, retirement planning, trust and fiduciary, foreign exchange, and payment services. In addition, it provides corporate banking solutions; corporate finance, equity capital markets, mergers and acquisitions, real estate finance, and ratings advisory services; and capital market products, such as commodities, exchange traded products, retail structures solutions, risk solutions, and equities. The company was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa. Absa Bank Limited is a subsidiary of Barclays Africa Group Limited.

column791: Afrimat Limited engages in the open pit mining, processing and the supply of various industrial minerals and materials to the industrial minerals, building, construction, road building, railroad, and mining sectors. It operates through Aggregates and Industrial Minerals, and Concrete Based Products segments. The Aggregates and Industrial Minerals segment offers metallurgical dolomite, metallurgical quartzite, metallurgical limestone, high calcium neutralization, limestone, agricultural lime, hydrated lime, un-slaked lime and calcium oxide, clinker ash, silica sand, ultra-fine limestone and dolomite, aggregates: crushed stone and sand, dolomite fillers, and stone dust. The Concrete Based Products segment offers building blocks and bricks, pavers, lintels, and readymix concrete. The company operates in the Western Cape, Eastern Cape, KwaZulu-Natal, Free State, Northern Cape, Gauteng, Limpopo, and Mpumalanga, as well as in Mozambique. The company was founded in 1963 and is headquartered in Bellville, South Africa.

Kumba Iron Ore Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the exploration, extraction, beneficiation, marketing, sale, and shipping of iron ore primarily in South Africa. The company produces iron ore at Sishen and Kolomela mines in the Northern Cape province. It also operates a port in Saldanha Bay, Western Cape. The company supplies its iron ore to the steel industry; and exports to China, Japan, and Korea, as well as various countries in Europe and the Middle East. The company was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa. Kumba Iron Ore Limited is a subsidiary of Anglo South Africa Capital (Proprietary) Limited.

Workforce Holdings Limited provides solutions for the supply, management, and administration of the human resources requirements of various industrial sectors in South Africa and internationally. The company operates in five segments: Staffing and Recruitment, Training and Consulting, Employee Health Management, Financial and Lifestyle Products, and Process Outsourcing segments. The Staffing and Recruitment segment provides staff and labor outsourcing solutions, and recruitment and specialist staffing services, including permanent and temporary placements, ad-response handling, executive search, and skills importing and exporting solutions. The Training and Consulting segment offers industry and job-specific skills assessments and training interventions to business and their employees in various industrial sectors. The Employee Health Management segment provides a range of occupational and primary health management services, and assistance and wellness services. The Financial and Lifestyle Products segment offers a range of lifestyle products and support services to employees and their families. The Process Outsourcing segment provides productive and functional business process outsourcing solutions, including the statutory and legal elements associated therewith. Accentuate Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the manufacture, distribution, and installation of flooring solutions primarily in South Africa. It also manufactures and supplies chemical cleaning and infrastructural maintenance solutions. It offers floor covering, accessories, self-levelling screeds, vinyl and wood maintenance, engineered and laminated wood floors, textile flooring, and transport flooring products. The company also provides customized chemical and adhesive solutions, including cleaning chemicals and equipment primarily for use in food industry, commercial property, industrial and mining, specialized and vehicle care, floor care, water purification, metal treatment, and cleaning equipment and parts washing. In addition, it offers water and waste water treatment chemicals and equipment comprising water treatment chemicals, ion exchange resins, RO chemicals, flocculants, membranes, waste water treatment plants, sewage treatment plants, design and consulting, turnkey solutions, and water installations. The company was formerly known as SAFIC Holdings Limited and changed its name to Accentuate Limited in May 2008. Accentuate Limited was founded in 1953 and is based in Steeledale, South Africa.

CSG Holdings Limited provides outsourced personnel, industrial and mining support, contract catering and food, and cleaning services in South Africa, Mozambique, and Malawi. The company operates in three segments: Staffing Solutions, Facilities Management, and Industrial and Mining Support Services. The Staffing Solutions segment offers temporary outsourced personnel, permanent placements, timekeeping, payroll, human resource, and industrial relations services, as well as contract workers, health and safety audits, employment equity, workforce restructuring, union related matters, and litigation management and support services. The Facilities Management segment manages staff canteens, as well as supplies meals to students, patients in hospitals, corporate head offices, mines, and construction sites. This segment also provides contract catering, events management, laundry, construction camp management, security, pest control and hygiene, and cleaning services. The Industrial and Mining Support Services segment offers plant cleaning, factory cleaning, industrial site and office cleaning, equipment hire, mining construction, and engineering services, as well as confined space safety surveillance - access control, procurement, conveyor system design and manufacturing, shutdown maintenance and management, spillage management, open cast mining, and turnkey projects services. It serves chemical and petro-chemical plants, mines, retail outlets, hospitals, schools, and various other clients, as well as industrial, manufacturing, and transport businesses. The company was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Pretoria, South Africa.

Zeder Investments Ltd. is a private equity arm of PSG Group Ltd. specializing in middle market investments in PIPEs transactions. The firm seeks to invest in unlisted securities of agricultural, food, beverages, grain, and related industries with a focus on agribusiness industry. It seeks to make investments in South Africa and neighboring countries. It invests between ZAR20 million ($2.74 million) and ZAR500 million($49.48 million) in companies with an enterprise values between ZAR50 million (4.95 million) and ZAR10000 million ($989.55 million), revenues between ZAR500 million($49.48 million) and ZAR30000 million ($2968.65 million), and EBITDA between ZAR10 million ($0.99 million) and ZAR2000 million ($197.91 million). The firm sources its capital through equity capital raised through the issuing of share to public shareholders. It invests through its personal capital. Zeder Investments Ltd. was founded in 2006 and is based in Stellenbosch, South Africa.

Nutritional Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, operates in the staple food manufacturing, water purification, and renewable energy sectors in the Republic of South Africa. Its Foods division engages in the manufacture and sale of staple dry food products primarily for the mass feeding market, as well as in contract manufacturing business. This division also offers catering products for the industrial catering market. The company's Healthcare Solutions division markets and distributes a range of chlorine free water purification products under license for point of use and industrial customers. This division's products include OneDrop, a point of use water purification drop; and BacSan, an industrial application for municipalities and other bulk water suppliers. Its Services division provides administration and management services. The company also markets and distributes a range of invertors, batteries, and accessories for solar farming, as well as for other industrial security customers; and distributes pharmaceutical, natural, and complementary medicines. Nutritional Holdings Limited is based in Cornubia, the Republic of South Africa.

enX Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides industrial, petrochemical, and fleet management and logistics products and services in South Africa, other African countries, the United Kingdom, Ireland, and internationally. The company operates through three segments: Equipment, Fleet, and Petrochemicals. The Equipment segment provides distribution, rental, and value added services for industrial and materials handling equipment. This segment distributes forklifts, BT warehousing equipment, heavy duty forklifts, and container handling equipment. It also manufactures, installs, and maintains diesel generators, as well as provides temporary power; and distributes various industrial and marine engines and components. In addition, this segment distributes professional woodworking equipment, and tooling and edging products, as well as provides associated services, such as blade sharpening and equipment maintenance services. The Fleet segment offers a range of passenger vehicle services, including leasing, fleet management, outsourcing, maintenance, warranty management, and vehicle tracking solutions. This segment also provides fleet management solutions for commercial vehicle fleet owners and logistics solutions through a network of workshops and panel repair shops. The Petrochemicals segment produces and markets oil lubricants; and distributes plastics, polymers, rubber, and specialty chemicals. The company was formerly known as Austro Group Limited and changed its name to enX Group Limited in January 2015. enX Group Limited was founded in 2007 and is based in Kempton Park, South Africa.

RARE Holdings Limited provides integrated fluid conveyance products and services to the energy, water, and chemical industries in South Africa, Zambia, Ghana, Botswana, Angola, Mali, Guinea, and the Democratic Republic of the Congo. It operates through four operating divisions: RARE Trading, RARE Pipeline Services, RARE Water Treatment Technology, and RARE Plastics. The RARE Trading division sells various products, such as steel and plastic pipes, fittings, couplings, and valves to the contractors or end users. It also offers cut-to-length, hot stamping, and colour-coding services to the market. The RARE Pipeline Services division provides pipeline installations and pipelining solutions to the mining and industrial sectors. It also supplies and installs various pipe systems, including steel, HDPE lined spool sections for slurry applications, PVC/PVDF, HDPE pipe installations, and cured in place pipe installations for pipeline rehabilitation, as well as double containment HDPE piping for cyanide applications in gold mining. The RARE Water Treatment Technology division provides services ranging from site investigation to design, manufacture, installation, and after-sales on-site support and service maintenance electrochemical treatment plants. These services include site investigation, feed water characterization, and process design; remote monitoring and control; site service maintenance contracts; and electrode management. The RARE Plastics division manufactures and distributes HDPE pipes and fittings. RARE Holdings Limited was founded in 1975 and is headquartered in Meyerton, South Africa. RARE Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Doculate Investments Proprietary Limited.

column791: Alert Steel Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the retail of steel and steel related products primarily in South Africa. It also provides building materials. The company operates approximately 10 Alert Express stores. It serves engineering, fabrication, manufacturing, construction, agricultural, mining, and parastatals and rural markets. The company was founded in 1979 and is based in Pretoria, South Africa.

South Ocean Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, primarily manufactures and sells low voltage electrical cables. The company offers electrical cables focusing on the wholesale sector; and light fittings, lamps/light bulbs, and electrical products, as well as electrical accessories, such as plugs, extension cords, and heaters principally to the construction, infrastructure development and housing, residential, industrial, and commercial markets. It also imports and distributes light fitting products, lamps, electrical accessories, and audio visual hardware and accessories. In addition, the company offers light fittings assembly services; and invests in properties. It sells its products to wholesalers and distributors who supply primarily to the building, construction, mining, and retail industries. South Ocean Holdings Limited was founded in 1989 and is based in Alrode, South Africa.

The company offers electrical cables focusing on the wholesale sector; and light fittings, lamps/light bulbs, and electrical products, as well as electrical accessories, such as plugs, extension cords, and heaters principally to the construction, infrastructure development and housing, residential, industrial, and commercial markets. It also imports and distributes light fitting products, lamps, electrical accessories, and audio visual hardware and accessories. In addition, the company offers light fittings assembly services; and invests in properties. It sells its products to wholesalers and distributors who supply primarily to the building, construction, mining, and retail industries. South Ocean Holdings Limited was founded in 1989 and is based in Alrode, South Africa.

Raubex Group Limited engages in material and construction businesses in Botswana, Mozambique, Namibia, South Africa, and Zambia. It operates commercial quarries, which supplies metallurgical dolomite, agricultural lime, and aggregates; and contract crushing and materials handling, and processing facilities for the mining industry. The company also engages in road surfacing and rehabilitation; road and civil infrastructure construction operations; earthworks; and infrastructure business, including renewable energy, rail, telecommunications, pipeline construction, and housing infrastructure projects. In addition, it is involved in manufacturing and laying asphalt, chip and spray, surface dressing, enrichment, and slurry seal products; and manufacturing and distributing bituminous products. Raubex Group Limited was founded in 1974 and is headquartered in Bloemfontein, South Africa.

Country Bird Holdings Limited, an agricultural company, engages in the integrated poultry and stock feed businesses in South Africa and other African regions. The company operates breeder sites, hatcheries, broiler sites, and processing plants. It provides frozen chicken under the brand names of Supreme Chicken, Spring Chicken, and Sublime Chicken. The company also produces a range of animal feed products for chickens, pigs, game, dairy cattle, beef cattle, and sheep, as well as ruminant supplements that are distributed through 280 outlets under the NUTRI Feeds brand name. Kelly Group Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides employment services, information technology (IT) skills development, and outsourcing solutions primarily in South Africa. It offers permanent recruitment, temporary staffing, executive and scarce skills searches, ad response handling, consulting, contact center management, skills development, online talent management solutions, candidate assessments, payroll services and compliance, recruitment process outsourcing, people resource planning, and interim management. The company also provides outsourced management, hospitality consulting, outsourced workforces, food and beverage, concierge, housekeeping, recruitment, and HR and IR consulting services for the hospital industry; temporary, contract, and permanent employment solutions to blue chip companies and SMEs in engineering and technical, executive search, financial, HR and procurement, and information communication technology areas; industrial staffing solutions; managed service employment solutions; and ICT training solutions to blue chip companies, the public sector, the youth in Africa, and others. Kelly Group Limited was founded in 1969 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. As of November 3, 2014, Kelly Group Limited operates as a subsidiary of Paracon Holdings Ltd.

Rolfes Holdings Limited manufactures and distributes chemical products to various industries in South Africa, the United States, Europe, Asia, and rest of Africa. It operates through Industrial, Water, Agricultural, Food, and Other segments. The Industrial segment manufactures and distributes alkyd resins, organic and inorganic pigments, additives, in-plant and point-of-sale dispersions, leather chemicals products and solutions, food fragrances, food flavourings, solvents, lacquer thinners, surfactants, cleaning solvents, creosotes, waxes, and other industrial chemicals. The Water segment is involved in quarrying and processing of beneficiated silica for the metallurgical, filtration, and construction industries; and provides specialized water purification solutions and products to industrial, agricultural, mining, home and personal care markets. The Agricultural segment manufactures and distributes herbicides, insecticides, fungicides, adjuvants, foliar feeds, enriched compost pellets, and soluble fertilizers used promoting general plant, root, foliage, and soil health. The Food segment imports and distributes chemicals used in the food, beverage, bakery, dairy, pharmaceutical, and cosmetics industries. The Other segment engages in the rental of property, plant, and equipment. The company also provides analytical data. The company was formerly known as Rolfes Technology Holdings Limited and changed its name to Rolfes Holdings Limited in November 2011. Rolfes Holdings Limited was founded in 1925 and is based in Illovo, the Republic of South Africa.

Ansys Limited develops, produces, distributes, and integrates technology-driven engineering solutions for the rail, mining and industrial, telecommunications, and defense and information security sectors in South Africa. The company offers information security, embedded solutions, helmet tracking camera sensors, weapon integration and control systems, mission computers and displays, and test equipment; and system design and integration, bespoke electronic hardware and software development, and contract manufacturing services. It also provides mobile rope testing units, gas detection instruments, collision awareness systems, and equipment and management software. In addition, the company offers trackside systems, such as vehicle identification, hot bearing detection, load profile monitoring, wheel profile monitoring, and integrated train condition; and monitoring systems, including asset tracking, health monitoring, RF ID tags, smart passes, and vandal proof solar power solutions. Further, it provides onboard systems comprising integrated and auxiliary display, train communication, and train definition units; and asset tracking systems. Additionally, the company is involved in the distribution of fiber and data cabling infrastructure, optical wireless broadband and RF products, and network and equipment monitoring solutions; designs, implements, and operates wireless network; designs and implements data centers; and structured cabling and fiber reticulation activities. Ansys Limited was founded in 1987 and is based in Centurion, South Africa.

Hulamin Limited manufactures and markets rolled and extruded aluminum products in South Africa and internationally. It operates in two segments, Hulamin Rolled Products and Hulamin Extrusions. The Hulamin Rolled Products segment offers a range of sheet, coil, and plate products for use in the packaging, automotive and transportation, engineering, and building and construction markets. This segment also produces rigid aluminum foil containers for the catering industry and for household use. Mondi Limited manufactures and sells packaging and paper products primarily in central Europe, Russia, North America, and the Republic of South Africa. The company operates through Packaging Paper, Fibre Packaging, Consumer Packaging, Uncoated Fine Paper, and South Africa Division segments. Its products include flexible packaging, bags and pouches, films, release liners, personal care components, corrugated packaging, industrial bags, barrier coatings, specialty kraft papers, sack kraft papers, containerboards, and office and professional printing papers. The company serves agriculture, automotive, building and construction, chemicals and dangerous goods, food and beverages, graphic and photographic, home and personal care, medical and pharmaceutical, office and professional printing, paper and packaging converting, pet care, retail and e-commerce, and shipping and transportation industries. B & W Instrumentation and Electrical Limited operates in the electrical and instrumentation industry in South Africa and Sub-Saharan Africa. It provides plant erection, equipment procurement, material supply, testing, commissioning, and maintenance services to plants in the infrastructure, mining, chemical, oil and gas, utilities, renewable energy, industrial, and power generation industries. The company offers construction management and supervision services, including planning, organizing, controlling, and monitoring the schedule, quality, and cost of the construction process. It also provides purchasing and inspection services for the client's equipment, as well as supplies bulk order material and miscellaneous items, such as cable, steelwork, light fittings, and instrument tubing. In addition, the company offers installation services comprising the physical erection of the electrical and instrumentation systems for the plants, including supply of tools and equipment; and provides calibration and commissioning services. Further, it offers earthing, lightning, and surge protection services. The company was founded in 1973 and is headquartered in Alberton, South Africa. As of April 22, 2014, B&W Instrumentation and Electrical Limited operates as a subsidiary of ELB Group Ltd.

WG Wearne Limited, together with its subsidiaries, supplies concrete products, aggregates, ready-mix concrete, precast concrete, and premix to the construction industry in South Africa. Its aggregate products include concrete stone, road stone, ballast stone, builders mix, crusher dust, crusher sand, dump rock, gabion stone, pit/building sand, plaster sand, river sand, ultra-thin friction course aggregates, and washed crusher sand. The company's ready-mix concrete products comprise self-levelling, self-compacting, colored and no fines, accelerated set, air entrained, fiber reinforced, pumping, extended workability and reduced slump loss, and high density concrete products, as well as screeds and mortars. It also provides mobile crushing and screening services; and laboratory services to ready-mix plants and quarries. The company was founded in 1910 and is headquartered in Cresta, South Africa.

Infrasors Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, mines, produces, and supplies industrial minerals to the steel, foundry, agriculture, ceramic, mining, building, and construction sectors in South Africa. It operates in the Silica, Dolomite and Limestone, and Other segments. The company offers metallurgical aggregate for the iron and steel industries; construction aggregate, and washed and super sand; stone dust for coal and agricultural industries; agricultural and industrial powders; metallurgical silica sand for foundries; silica sand for tile adhesive and glass industries, and golf courses and recreational markets; and building sand. It owns and operates the Lyttelton Centurion, Marble Hall, Delf Sand, and Delf Silica Coastal mines. The company was incorporated in 2007 and is headquartered in Lyttelton, South Africa. As of March 1, 2013, Infrasors Holdings Limited operates as a subsidiary of Afrimat Limited.

column791: Stefanutti Stocks Holdings Limited operates as a construction company in South Africa, sub-Saharan Africa, and the United Arab Emirates. It operates through Roads, Pipelines and Mining Services; Mechanical and Electrical; Structures; and Building segments. The Roads, Pipelines and Mining Services segment constructs roads, terraces for new developments, mining infrastructure and rehabilitation, bulk pipelines, and mine residue disposal facilities, as well as provides fiber optic cable trenching, open-pit contract mining, and other municipal services. The Mechanical and Electrical segment undertakes mechanical and electrical installation and construction works. The Structures segment undertakes civil engineering, structural concrete construction, geotechnical, and marine infrastructure construction projects. The Building segment constructs commercial, industrial, residential, and leisure buildings, including residential developments for mining and industrial companies, as well as low-cost and affordable housing for the public sector. The company was founded in 1971 and is based in Kempton Park, South Africa.

Brikor Limited, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and supplies building and construction materials in South Africa. It serves customers in housing, residential, commercial, industrial, civil engineering, and infrastructure projects. Brikor Limited was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Nigel, South Africa. Brikor Limited is a subsidiary of Estate of Garnett van Niekerk Parkin.

column791: Protech Khuthele Holdings Limited provides construction and related services to the mining firms, government, and state-owned entities in South Africa. The company operates through three segments: Contracting, Geotechnical Laboratory, and Readymix. The Contracting segment offers bulk earthworks, roads and civil engineering contract, plant hire, impact compaction, and logistical services. The Geotechnical Laboratory segment provides geotechnical laboratory and surveying services. The Readymix segment supplies readymixed concrete and offers pumping services. The company is based in Lanseria, South Africa.

Huge Group Limited, an investment holding company, provides voice connectivity, messaging, and telephone management services in South Africa. The company offers fixed location voice services that make use of the GSM last mile provided by the mobile network operators to the small and medium enterprise; small and home office; and residential markets. It also provides voice, network connectivity, and payment services, including connectivity to the card payment terminals of commercial banks using managed and dual SIM connectivity over GSM data networks; and other services, such as ATMs, integrated points-of-sale, medical/script verifications, telemetry applications, micro-lending applications, and cash vaults. In addition, the company markets and sells network and data communications products and services, including Internet data services, managed network solutions, branch connectivity and hosting services, and Website and system development services. Further, it develops software and router products for third parties; and develops and licenses software for real time, permission based, and targeted advertising to mobile phones. The company primarily has operations in the Western Cape, Eastern Cape, KwaZulu-Natal, and Bloemfontein regions. Huge Group Limited was founded in 1993 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.
