Ellies Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the manufacture, import, and distribution of television (TV) and video equipment-related products, and satellite and associated equipment under the Ellies and Elsat brand names in the Republic of South Africa. The company operates through four segments: Goods and Services, Properties, Manufacturing, and Infrastructure. It develops, manufactures, and sells terrestrial antennae; and light metal products, such as wall brackets, shelving, satellite and terrestrial mounting brackets, and satellite dishes, as well as LED and plasma mounts. The company also offers wizard remote blaster and video senders; cryovacing and plastic blister packaging products; and thermal, electric and other solutions through alternative energy products. In addition, it provides commercial lighting, industrial audio system, and satellite and TV distribution systems; and rents fibre linked infrastructures, communal signal distribution systems, satellite decoders, video and audio systems, generators, inverters, and energy saving products. Further, the company offers commercial turnkey solutions inclusive of full project management, customised design, supply and installation of triple play fibre optic and coaxial cable solutions. Additionally, it is involved in the construction of water and waste water treatment plants. The company serves property developers, building owners, architects, corporates and the hospitality industry. The company was founded in 1979 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Imbalie Beauty Limited operates as a franchisor, retailer, distributor, and service provider of skincare, nail care, and other beauty products primarily in South Africa. RBA Holdings Limited develops housing properties primarily in South Africa. It operates through two segments, Property Development Activities and Sectional Title Rental Activities. The company's principal product offerings include bonded homes sold to prospective new homeowners; and the development and delivery of rental units to institutional market participants and property investors that hold residential rental portfolios. It engages in the provision of land procurement, town planning and urban design, architectural and civil engineering expertise, and legal administration services for the property development and construction process, as well as construction, and marketing and sales services. The company was founded in 1997 and is based in Braamfontein, South Africa.

BSi Steel Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the processing, warehouse, distribution, and sale of steel and allied products in South Africa and the rest of Africa. It operates in four segments: Stockists, Bulk Sales, Exporting, and Other. The company offers flat products, including hot and cold rolled, galvanized, color-coated, aluzinc, and electro-plated products; and plates, such as structural grade, quenched and tempered, and boiler plates. It also provides long products comprising beams and columns, channels, angles, and reinforcing bars; and round, square, and flat bars, as well as light sections. In addition, the company offers corrugated, IBR, and wide-span roofing products; round, square, and rectangular tubing products; lipped channels; slit strips and precision blanks; cut to length sheets and plates; and profile cut plates and sheets. Further, it engages in the rental of property. BSi Steel Limited was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Pietermaritzburg, South Africa.

column787: Corner of Grayston Drive & Benmore Drive
column791: Blue Label Telecoms Limited engages in the virtual distribution of electronic tokens of value and transactional activities in South Africa, India, Mexico, and the United Kingdom. It operates through South African Distribution, International Distribution, Mobile, and Solutions segments. The South African Distribution segment distributes prepaid products and transactional services, including starter packs, physical airtime vouchers, virtual vouchers, bulk print solutions, prepaid electricity and water vouchers, international calling cards, bill payment, ticketing, lotto, financial services, prepaid electricity vending, arrears collection, meter audits, data cleansing, debt collection, hybrid discounted airtime contract, and network postpaid contract services, as well as vending machine, kiosk touch screen, POS terminal, gateway for integrated POS, and mobi merchant solutions to the South African wholesale and retail markets. The International Distribution segment offers physical prepaid products and starter packs; label investments; PINless recharge, direct top-up, and payment services; and service aggregation and distribution, online payment processing, and money transfer services through mobile, POS, and Web to telecom/DTH operators, and various service providers and banks. The Mobile segment provides mobile transactional ecosystem and services provisioning platform delivering mobile-centric products and services through mobile channel, including location-based and WASP services, and music and digital content. The Solutions segment markets cellular and financial products and services through outbound telemarketing and other channels; and data and analytics services, as well as provides inbound customer care and technical support services. The company was founded in 2001 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

It offers wood-based panels under the Kayreed Board and Timber, and Davidson's Discount Boards brands for the furniture, shop-fitting, and kitchen manufacturing and installation industries, as well as to other wood-based panel distributors. The company also provides packaging consumables and machinery through its outlets in Western Cape and Gauteng for various customers, including manufacturers, agriculture, home industries, and small businesses under the Packit Packaging Solutions trade name. KayDav Group Limited is headquartered in Cape Town, South Africa.

Calgro M3 Holdings Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the mixed-use/integrated residential properties development activities in South Africa. It operates through three segments: Property Development, Professional Services, and Memorial Parks. The company develops integrated, affordable, mid-high income housing properties; and memorial parks, as well as rents residential properties. It also offers land acquisition, town planning, architecture, civil infrastructure project management, installation, and home marketing and construction services. The company serves the government, financial institutions, and the general public. Calgro M3 Holdings Limited was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Bryanston, South Africa.

ARB Holdings Limited, an investment holding company, engages in the trading and distribution of electrical, lighting, and related products. It operates through three segments: Electrical, Lighting, and Corporate. The company provides power and instrumentation cables, overhead line hardware and conductors, insulators, transformers, general electrical contracting materials, and general low-voltage products to large and heavy industry, government and parastatal, construction, mining, electrical contractor, and domestic/do-it-yourself (DIY) markets. It also imports and distributes incandescent, energy saving, LED, and fluorescent lamps; light fittings; commercial and project lighting products; and a range of electrical accessories, as well as ancillary products, including fans and lighting components to retail chains, independent DIY chains, hardware stores, specialized lighting shops, and electrical wholesalers. In addition, the company sells computer hardware; and provides specialist IT hardware, and software and support services, as well as holds and rents a portfolio of 15 properties. ARB Holdings Limited was founded in 1980 and is based in Durban, South Africa.

Mazor Group Limited designs, supplies, and installs structural steelwork and aluminum facades for the industrial, construction, and infrastructure markets in the Republic of South Africa. It operates through three divisions: Steel, Aluminium, and Glass. The Steel division designs, supplies, and erects structural steel frames for industrial and retail buildings, including shopping centers, warehouses, buildings, bridges, and architectural work. The Aluminium division designs, manufactures, and installs aluminum structures, such as doors, windows, shop fronts, facades, balustrades, and custom solutions for blue-chip construction groups. This division also supplies aluminum fenestration systems. The Glass division manufactures and distributes laminated, toughened safety, and processed glasses. Mazor Group Limited was founded in 1981 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Consolidated Infrastructure Group Limited, an infrastructure-focused company, operates in the power, mining, logistics, and waste management sectors in Africa and the Middle East. The company operates through Power, Building Materials, Oil and Gas, and Rail divisions. It supplies high voltage infrastructure for governments, utilities, municipalities, and mining and finance houses, as well as the industrial sector; and provides power maintenance services in the renewable energy sector. The company also mines, manufactures, and supplies face, semi-faced, and plaster clay bricks, as well as various concrete roof tiles to the building sector, including developers, contractors, and wholesalers; and aggregates, such as sand, gravel, and crushed stone to commercial and civil building contractors. In addition, it collects, recycles, and disposes oil-based waste created during the drilling process for the industrial and natural resources exploration sectors. Further, Consolidated Infrastructure Group Limited provides rail infrastructure service, including railway and power solutions, and maintenance. The company was formerly known as Buildworks Group Limited and changed its name to Consolidated Infrastructure Group Limited in September 2010. Consolidated Infrastructure Group Limited is based in Sandton, South Africa.

Vunani Limited provides financial products and services primarily in South Africa. The company operates through Fund Management, Asset Administration, Advisory Services, Institutional Securities Broking, Private Equity, and Private Wealth and Investments segments. It offers single asset class products, such as managed equity, bonds, inflation-linked bonds and property; multi-asset class products comprising absolute return and alternative return; and fundamental and market cap indexation beta products. The company also offers a trading platform for high net worth individuals to trade their portfolios, derivatives, and hedging instruments; manages portfolios on behalf of private clients; a range of products, including geared derivatives and money market accounts; and absolute, balanced, and directional funds. In addition, it provides investment banking services, such as corporate advisory services to public sector entities, corporations, entrepreneurs, municipalities, financial sponsors, and boards of directors; and capital-raising services. Further, the company offers stockbroking services to institutional and retail clients. The company was incorporated in 1997 and is based in Sandton, South Africa. Vunani Limited is a subsidiary of Vunani Group (Pty) Ltd.

Insimbi Refractory and Alloy Supplies Limited provides ferrous and non-ferrous alloys, and refractory materials for the steel, aluminum, cement, and foundry industries in South Africa and internationally. It operates through Foundry, Refractory, Steel, and Plastics segments. The Foundry segment supplies various alloys and ancillary raw materials, such as foundry sand and ceramic ducting to ferrous and non-ferrous foundries, including heavy-duty foundries, automotive foundries, electroplating specialists, etc. The Refractory segment supplies specialized ceramic refractory linings to cement, paper and pulp, steel, and platinum industries. The Steel segment supplies various alloys that include non-ferrous alloys to the steel and stainless steel industry. The Plastics segment engages in the blowmoulding of plastic containers for the chemical, agricultural, and food industries. The company was founded in 1970 and is headquartered in Germiston, South Africa.

Keaton Energy Holdings Limited, a coal mining company, engages in the mining, exploration, extraction, and processing of coal. It explores for thermal and metallurgical coal, and anthracite. The company's flagship project is the Vanggatfontein colliery that is located to the south-east of Delmas, Mpumalanga. It also operates other projects in KwaZulu-Natal in South Africa. The company was founded in 2006 and is based in Bryanston, South Africa. As per the transaction announced on February 2, 2017, Keaton Energy Holdings Limited operates as a subsidiary of Wescoal Holdings Limited.

Pioneer Food Group Ltd, together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells food, beverage, and related products for human and animal consumption in South Africa. It operates through Essential Foods, Groceries, International, and Other segments. The company produces breakfast cereals, rusks, cake mixes, baking aids and desserts, dried fruits, nuts, sweet and savory spreads, processed salads, fruit juices, fruit concentrate mixtures, ice tea, bottled water, and dairy fruit blends. It also manufactures and sells wheat, maize, and pasta products; and supplies rice, beans and legumes, and other dried vegetables, as well as engages in bakery operations. The company sells its products primarily under the Weet-Bix, Liqui-Fruit, Ceres, Sasko, Safari, Spekko, and White Star brand names to the wholesale, retail, and trade customers. Pioneer Food Group Ltd also exports its products to approximately 60 countries worldwide. The company was incorporated in 1996 and is based in Tyger Valley, South Africa.

Clientele Limited provides financial products and services in South Africa. It operates in four segments: Long-Term Insurance, Investment Contracts, Short-Term Insurance, and Loans Business. The company underwrites, markets, and distributes insurance and investment products principally on a direct distribution basis. It offers funeral, hospital, legal, and life insurance products. The company also provides personal loans; and investment solutions, which comprise wealth, guaranteed income, and growth plans, as well as financial advisory services. In addition, it offers short-term insurance products, such as personal and business lines legal insurance policies. The company is headquartered in Morningside, South Africa. Clientele Limited is a subsidiary of Pickent Investments Limited.

Grand Parade Investments Limited is a private equity firm specializing in incubation, PIPE's, industry consolidation, recapitalizations, buyouts, and growth capital investments. It considers investments in middle market, mature, turnaround, and emerging growth stages. The firm typically invests in leisure, tourism, and gaming sectors and also considers investments in property, retail, food, manufacturing, and entertainment. It seeks to invest in Africa with a focus on South Africa  and Western Cape. The firm primarily invests between R$10 million ($0.84 million) and R$1000 million ($84.98 million) in companies with enterprise value greater than R$300 million ($25.50 million). The firm prefers to take a board seat in its portfolio companies. It may enter into joint ventures and other similar alliances, whereby it forms partnerships with such entities, contributing not only capital, but also providing strategic managerial input. The firm seeks to take more than 20 per cent stake, however a smaller stake is also considered where there is the potential to increase such stake in the future. It seeks to make balance sheet investments. Grand Parade Investments Limited was founded in 1997 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa.

Alaris Holdings Limited engages in the design, manufacture, and sale of antennas in South Africa and internationally. The company provides broadband antennas, as well as other related radio frequency products to system integrators, frequency spectrum regulators, and players in the homeland security space for use in the communication, frequency spectrum monitoring, test and measurement, electronic warfare, and other specialized markets. It also offers antenna products, serving military and public safety markets; and integrated broadcasting systems for radio and TV broadcasters for use in digital compression platforms for digital terrestrial television, direct to home and Internet protocol television, signal distribution, and multiscreen, as well as over-the-top systems. The company was formerly known as Poynting Holdings Limited and changed its name to Alaris Holdings Limited in May 2015. Alaris Holdings Limited was founded in 1990 and is based in Centurion, South Africa.

column786: Corner of Hulley and Gewel Avenue
column791: Wescoal Holdings Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in mining, processing, supplying, selling, and distributing coal and coal-related products primarily in South Africa. The company operates through two divisions, Mining and Trading. It is involved in the exploration, beneficiation, and mining of coal; and trading of coal and related products, including small nuts, industrial peas, duff, and anthracite. The company's flagship mine is the Elandspruit colliery that contains five mineable coal seams located on the old Witbank road in the Mpumalanga province, as well as holds interests in the Intibane colliery and Khanyisa colliery mines. It also provides logistical requirements for the sourcing, distribution, and delivery of coal products to the general industry with emphasis on road transportation. The company sources and supplies coal to clients in power generation and manufacturing sectors. Wescoal Holdings Limited is based in Isando, South Africa.

Mvelaserve Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides outsourced business support services in South Africa and internationally. The company offers a range of integrated services to access various industries and sectors, including security, facilities management, cleaning, and catering. It offers facilities management services; security services to the mining industry, as well as assets-in-transit services; outsourced contract-cleaning services, and hygiene and laundry services; catering services; and monitoring services for pay-out machines (LPMs) for the national gambling board, as well as data collection equipment in the LPM industry. The company also provides water purification equipment, as well as designs, manufactures, installs, tests, and commissions water treatment plants; and franchises King Pie brand, and manufactures and supplies King Pie product range to retail and forecourt markets. In addition, the company offers hygiene, packaging, and ingredient solutions for the food preparation and cleaning sectors; and pothole and road surface repair solutions to conventional patching. It serves financial institutions, mining houses, and retailers, as well as parastatals and government departments. The company is headquartered in Centurion, South Africa.

Clover Industries Limited produces and distributes dairy and non-dairy beverage consumer products. It operates through Dairy fluids, Concentrated Products, Ingredients, Non-alcoholic Beverages, and Fermented Products and Desserts segments. The company offers dairy fluid products, such as fresh milk, UHT milk, steri milk, ultra-pasteurized milk, and cream; concentrated dairy products, including cheese, butter, condensed milk, and retail milk powders; bulk milk powders, bulk butter, bulk condensed milk, bulk creamers, calf feed substitutes, whey powders, and buttermilk powders; non-alcoholic beverage products comprising fruit juices, dairy fruit mixes, flavored milk, water, and ice tea; and yoghurt, maas, custard, and other dessert products. It also provides laboratory services for dairy and dairy-related industries; distributes and sells chilled and ambient consumer products of other brands; and manufactures and distributes soya based milk alternatives and a range of functional food products. The company serves customers through its distribution centers in South Africa, as well as exports its products. The company was formerly known as National Co-operative Dairies Limited and changed its name to Clover Industries Limited in 2003. Clover Industries Limited was founded in 1898 and is based in Roodepoort, South Africa.

Curro Holdings Limited develops, acquires, and manages independent schools in South Africa and Namibia. It operates through Curro, Meridian, and Embury segments. The company operates nursery, primary, and high schools, as well as provides balanced academics, sport, and culture services. It operates Curro schools that accommodate learners from age 3 to grade 12; Meridian and Curro Academy schools, which accommodate learners from age 5 to grade 12; and Curro Castles nursery schools, which accommodate learners from 3 months to 5 years old, as well as Curro Select schools. The company also operates Embury Institute for Teacher Training, a private higher education institution that offers full-time teacher education qualifications, as well as in-service training for practicing teachers. As of December 31, 2016, it operated 54 campuses and 127 schools accommodating 47,589 learners, which include the teachers training college accommodating approximately 950 students. The company was founded in 1998 and is based in Durbanville, the Republic of South Africa. Curro Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of PSG Financial Services Ltd.

Mpact Limited manufactures and sells paper and plastic packaging products in South Africa and other African regions. It operates through Paper and Plastics segments. The Paper segment offers recycled-based packaging and industrial paper grades, such as containerboards and carton boards; and a range of printed and unprinted converted corrugated products, including boards for use in the manufacture of corrugated packaging, corrugated boxes, die-cut cases, folded glued cases, trays, and point-of-sale displays. It also sells Baywhite, a white top Kraftliner; and recycles paper through various recovered paper sources comprising pre- and post-consumer material sourced through a range of paper pickup programs. This segment markets its packaging and industrial paper products to corrugated board and box producers, and other containerboard converters; carton boards to folding carton converters and other producers of industrial products, as well as the manufacturers of cards and book covers; and corrugated products to producers of agricultural, fast moving consumer goods (FMCG), and other durable and non-durable goods. The Plastics segment manufactures various plastic packaging products, such as polyethylene terephthalate (PET) preforms, bottles, and jars; closures for carbonated soft drinks, water, and food; and plastic jumbo bins, environmental wheelie bins, and plastic pallets and crates. This segment also provides plastic FMCG containers, including bottles, tubs, jars, and closures; and styrene and PET trays, and clear plastic films, as well as recycled-based PET products. It serves the food, beverage, personal care, home care, pharmaceutical, agricultural, environmental, and retail markets. The company is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Transaction Capital Limited provides non-deposit taking financial services in South Africa. It operates through two divisions, SA Taxi and Transaction Capital Risk Services. The SA Taxi division provides finance, insurance, and other related products primarily for small-to-medium enterprise (SMEs) in the fixed route minibus taxi industry. The Transaction Capital Risk Services division offers customer management and capital solutions, including the collection of accounts receivable across credit lifecycle; business support and working capital finance; and personal credit information, as well as tailor-made services. This division works with large consumer credit providers across various industries, such as banking, credit retail, telecommunications, insurance, specialist lending, the public sector, and SMEs. Transaction Capital Limited is based in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Gooderson Leisure Corporation Limited, an investment holding company, owns and manages various leisure destinations in South Africa. It operates through Hotels and Lodges, and Timeshare divisions. The company manages and provides accommodation, conference and wedding facilities, food and beverage, and restaurant services to leisure, international, and conference tourists in KwaZulu Natal, Limpopo, Gauteng, and Mpumalanga provinces. Its leisure portfolio comprises the Tropicana Hotel, and the Beach Hotel in Durban; the Drakensberg Gardens Golf & Spa Resort in southern Drakensberg; and the Bushlands Game Lodge, and the DumaZulu Lodge & Traditional Village in Hluhluwe. The company's leisure portfolio also includes the Natal Spa Hot Springs & Leisure resort in Paulpietersburg; the Monks Cowl Golf Resort in Central Drakensberg; Kloppenheim Country Estate hotel in Dullstroom; Fabz Garden Hotel & Conference Centre in Johannesburg; and the SanRock Resort & Conference Centre in Modimolle. In addition, it manages timeshare resorts that include Fairways, Riverbend Chalets, and Mountainview Cottages at Drakensberg Gardens; Silversands I, II, III Lifestyle Resort in Durban; and Mtunzini Forest Lodge Lifestyle Resort at Mtunzini. The company was founded in 1957 and is headquartered in Durban, South Africa.

Times Media Group Limited operates as a media company in South Africa and internationally. The company's Media division publishes newspapers under the Sunday Times, The Times, Business Day, Times Media Live, Sowetan, Sunday World, Daily Dispatch, and The Herald brands; Times Media community newspapers; and magazines under the Financial Mail, South African Home Owner, Picasso Headline, MIMS, and other titles. Its Broadcasting and Content division is involved in the television broadcasting and production activities under the Business Day TV, Home Channel, Ignition, and Ochre Media names; radio broadcasting activities primarily under the Rise FM and Vuma 103 FM names; film distribution activities; production and distribution of recorded music and music copyrights; and provision of airport advertising, and digital marketing and media agency services. This division also offers Learning Channel that provides education solutions. The company's Retail Solutions division offers commercial print products and services; owns and operates the retail image libraries; manufactures CDs and digital versatile discs; and provides customized logistics, debt risk management, and rights management services to the music and home entertainment industries. It is also involved in the retail printing and home entertainment businesses. Times Media Group Limited is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. The company's Media division publishes newspapers under the Sunday Times, The Times, Business Day, Times Media Live, Sowetan, Sunday World, Daily Dispatch, and The Herald brands; Times Media community newspapers; and magazines under the Financial Mail, South African Home Owner, Picasso Headline, MIMS, and other titles. Cartrack Holdings Limited provides fleet management, stolen vehicle recovery, and insurance telematics services in South Africa. The company offers Bike Recovery, a wireless, self-powered, and waterproof tracking device for stolen motorbike recovery; Bike Track, a real-time GPS/GSM telematics solution for commercial motorbikes; Bike Track with the stolen vehicle recovery services; and Asset Track, a wireless and self-powered GPS/GSM tracking unit, which helps you track and monitor the movement of movable asset. It also provides Drive vision, an on-board dual camera system that comprises a primary camera that records video footage with a 120-degree exterior view of the road ahead, and plus secondary driver camera that provides a 160-degree view of the inside of the vehicle cab; Communicator, a software application for mobile tablets and phones that combines communication, navigation, tracking and task management technologies into one solution. In addition, the company offers Mi-Fleet, an administrative and vehicle cost accounting software. It also operates in Europe, South East Asia, the United States, and New Zealand. The company was founded in 2001 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa. Cartrack Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Onecell Holdings Proprietary Limited.

Novus Holdings Limited provides commercial printing and manufacturing businesses in South Africa and internationally. The company operates in two segments, Printing and Other. It offers gravure, heatset, coldset, sheet-fed, and digital printing services. The company prints inserts, newspapers, magazines, commercial works, annual reports, examination materials, ballots, books, and directories, as well as security products, such as election ballots, examination materials and assessments, and other security related printing products. The company was founded in 1905 and is headquartered in Milnerton, South Africa. Novus Holdings Limited is a subsidiary of Media24 Proprietary Limited.

The company has elected to be taxed as a REIT and would not be subject to federal corporate income taxes if it distributes at least 90% of its taxable income to its stockholders. Newpark REIT Limited was founded in 2015 and is based in Houghton Estate, South Africa.

BID Corporation Limited operates as foodservice solutions supplier worldwide. The company operates through Foodservice Australia, Foodservice United Kingdom, Foodservice Europe, Foodservice Emerging Markets, Bidvest Services, and Corporate segments. It distributes and wholesales ambient, chilled and frozen food, fresh produce, meat, and related non-food products to operators in the foodservice and catering industries. The company was founded in 1988 and is based in Johannesburg, South Africa. BID Corporation Limited is a subsidiary of Bidvest Group Limited.

Global Asset Management Limited, through its subsidiaries, provides forklift truck rental and maintenance services in the Republic of South Africa. It also sells forklift trucks; and offers project management, corporate, and other services. In addition, the company provides project and structured finance, asset finance, export credit finance, DTI grants, and loan and/or working capital facility restructuring services, as well as property development services, including designing and implementing funding structures for residential and commercial property developments. Further, it offers debt and mezzanine capital for large infrastructure projects; and engages in renewable energy and energy efficiency equipment installation funding businesses, as well as rubber and plastic recycling activities. The company was founded in 1992 and is based in Roodepoort, the Republic of South Africa. Global Asset Management Limited is a subsidiary of Inshare Proprietary Limited.

Sasol Inzalo Public Limited (RF), through its investment in Sasol Limited, operates as an integrated energy and chemicals company in South Africa and internationally. It manufactures and sells base chemical products, including fertilizers, polymers, and solvents; performance chemicals, such as surfactants, surfactant intermediates, fatty alcohols, linear alkyl benzene, short-chain linear alpha olefins, ethylene, mineral oil-based and synthetic paraffin waxes, cresylic acids, and carbon solutions, as well as high-purity alumina and specialty gases; fuels and oils, such as automotive and industrial lubricants, greases, cleansers and degreases, and automotive and burner fuels; and polyethylene, polypropylene, polyvinyl chloride polymers, as well as explosives. The company also offers low-carbon electricity; operates coal mines that supply feedstock, as well as coal to the international power generation customers; and develops and manages the upstream interests in oil and gas exploration and production in Mozambique, South Africa, Canada, Gabon, and Australia. Its products are used in the production of hot-melt adhesives, car products, microchip coatings, printing inks, household and industrial paints, mobile phone circuit boards, transport fuels, compact discs, medical lasers, sun creams, perfumes, and plastic bottles. The company was incorporated in 2007 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.

Visual International Holdings Limited engages in the property holding and development business in the Republic of South Africa. It operates in three segments: Property Services, Property Investment, and Property Development. The company primarily develops and sells residential, commercial, and retail projects. It is also involved in letting residential properties; and providing management, administration, and consulting services on development projects. The company was formerly known as Presto Financing Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Visual International Holdings Limited in October 2013. Visual International Holdings Limited was founded in 1983 and is based in Stellenberg, the Republic of South Africa.

Dis-Chem Pharmacies Limited owns and operates a chain of pharmacy stores, family clinics, and medication centers. The company operates through Retail and Wholesale segments. It offers dispensary products, including diagnostics, first aid, mobility and incontinence, and OTC remedies; beauty products, including beauty accessories, color cosmetics, face care, fragrance, and skin care; toiletries products, including bath care, bathroom, body care, deodorants, foot care, hair care, intimate care, oral care, and shaving products; vitamins and nutraceuticals, and homeopathic and herbal products; sports supplements, and sports equipment and aids; and foods and specialized diet. The company also provides electrical products, including heating and cooling, household, and lifestyle; household products, including cleaners and fresheners, homeware, insecticides, kitchen, kitchen tools, purifiers, storage, and veterinary; and seasonal cards and gifts. It also sells products online, as well as operates hair and beauty salons. Dis-Chem Pharmacies Limited has approximately 101 stores in South Africa; and two partner stores in Namibia. The company was founded in 1978 and is headquartered in Midrand, South Africa.

Premier Food and Fishing Limited, through its subsidiaries, engages in harvesting, processing, and marketing fish and fish-related, and general food products in South Africa, the United States, the Far East, Europe, and South Africa. It operates through Fishing, Aquaculture, and Services segments. The company's products include rock lobsters, octopus, squids, abalones, pilchards, hakes, general food products, and organic liquid fertilizers, as well as anchovy and pelagic products. It also provides processing and marketing, and cold storage services. Premier Food and Fishing Limited offers its products under the South Atlantic, Sea Diamond, Atlantic Abalone, SSF, and Seagro brands. The company was formerly known as Sekunjalo Industrial Holdings Proprietary Limited. Premier Food and Fishing Limited was founded in 1952 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Premier Food and Fishing Limited is a subsidiary of African Equity Empowerment Investments Limited.

Sea Harvest Group Limited engages in the fishing and food business servicing retail and foodservice customers. Its activities include the fishing of Cape Hake and Shark Bay prawns, processing of the catch into frozen and chilled seafood, and marketing of these products. The company owns and operates a fleet of 18 vessels, which include single and twin fresh fish trawlers, factory freezer trawlers, and access to in-shore trawlers that catch and process Cape Hake, as well as other by-catch species, such as kingklip and monk. It also has 11 prawn vessels, which catch and process prawns, scallops, crabs, and related by-catch species in Australia. The company distributes various chilled and frozen food products through distribution network; and to local supermarket chains in South Africa, as well as supplies its products to 22 countries, including countries within the European Union, North America, and Australia. It also operates as an agent for Findus, a frozen food brand; and Quorn, a meat-substitute brand, as well as imports and distributes frozen seafood to the catering and hospitality industry. The company was formerly known as Sea Harvest Holdings Proprietary Limited and changed its name to Sea Harvest Group Limited in February 2017. The company was founded in 1964 and is based in Cape Town, South Africa. Sea Harvest Group Limited is a subsidiary of Brimco Proprietary Limited.

Pembury Lifestyle Group Limited provides private education and associated services to pre-primary, primary, and high school students. The company operates through PLG Allens View Academy, PLG Ballito Academy, PLG Hartbeespoort Academy, PLG Mellow Oaks Academy, PLG Northriding Academy, PLG Raslouw Academy, PLG Springs Academy, and PLG Willow View Academy segments. Its schools offer pre-primary, primary, and high school education, as well as provide aftercare, tuition, and boarding services. The company operates a total of 19 schools on the 7 campuses. Pembury Lifestyle Group Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Johannesburg, South Africa.
